ogs or forums and your communication with other users of Owrners.\r\n </li></ul><div><font color=\"#374151\"><b>Information We Collect Automatically.</b> We gather data whenever you connect to, navigate, view or otherwise interact with the Site including the data on transactions and communications with other users, searches made, the pages visited, browsed and scrolled, the clicks made and other actions on the Site. We also, collect, use and process the information relating to such usage, including geo-location information, IP address, device and connection information, operating system, session duration, language, currency and keyboard setting, browser information and web-log information, and the URLs of the web pages you’ve viewed or engaged with before or after visiting the Site. We also obtain and process information concerning the usage of cookies and other similar technologies as outlined below.\r\n </font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\">Also for enhancing your online experience at Owrners, we have introduced impression reporting. As you look at our ads, we collect user Global Unique Identifier, HTTP request details such as; user agent, IP, host, URL, country/continent from which request was made, browser information, device/operating system/operating system version.\r\n </font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\"><b>Information We Receive from Third Parties.</b> We receive information from third party vendors and/or other commercially and/or publicly available sources, such as:</font></div><ul><li><font color=\"#374151\">Third party vendors who give us data to augment the data we gather about you, as permitted by the law. For instance, we get fraud and security alerts from service providers for our fraud control and appraisal purposes. We also obtain some information about you, for example information about your organization and your job title from the enrichment service providers in order to improve and individualize your experience and offer you the services that may interest you as well as from advertising and marketing partners to manage and monitor our campaigns.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">In case you register with your account or connect, link, or login through a third party account like Google, Facebook, LinkedIn among others, we receive information from the third party service including your registration and profile information. Such information may, for instance, include your email address, name and profile picture; however, it may differ and depends on that service or as per your privacy settings you have set for that service.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">If any other third party provides a report and/or complaint on you or your activities on Owrners, we may receive information concerning the particular report and/or complaint, consider and respond to it.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">If you select the option of inviting contacts from your Google Workspace directory, then we will have the ability to view details of contacts based on the permission set by you in Google Workspace. We will employ this data to enable you to invite your contacts to your Owrners account. Internal use of the data will also be made with the help of aggregated anonymised information.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">If you connect other accounts or have connected your account with other third-party applications, systems, tools or products, we will get some information about you depending on your settings on those third parties. \r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">We also obtain some information about you if you are invited to Owrners by another user (for instance, when using our collaboration tools and the referral program), in this case, we will receive limited information, including your email address or other contact details, and will use it for the same purpose it was provided and as provided by this Policy.\r\n </font></li></ul><div><font color=\"#374151\">When we use your personal information, we link it to other information we have collected or obtained from other sources and for the uses stated in this Policy.</font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>3. Our Legal Basis for Using Your Personal Information</b></span>\r\n </font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\">Depending on the laws applicable to our company, all processing of your personal information will be based on a “legal basis” for processing. In the majority of cases, processing will be justified on the legal basis that:\r\n </font></div><ul><li><font color=\"#374151\">you have agreed that we may use your personal details for a particular purpose;\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">our use of your personal information is most important for the performance of a contract or for taking steps at your request prior to entering into such a contract with you (e. g. to fulfill the services you have ordered);\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">the processing is required to meet the legal requirement or legal obligation that exist in the company (for instance, prevention of fraud); or\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">the processing is required in the exercise of our legitimate interests as a business such as enhancing our services to you, but only when those interests can be pursued in a manner that does not override your interests and fundamental rights and in any event only in proportion.\r\n </font></li></ul><div><font color=\"#374151\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">4. How Do We Use The Information Collected?</span>\r\n </b></font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\">We will use your personal information for the following purposes:\r\n </font></div><ul><li><font color=\"#374151\">To deliver to you excellent service and security, for the functioning of the Site, to meet our contractual and other commitments to you and for the purpose of enhancing and customizing our service. For instance, we employ the data for identity confirmation. We also use this information to create and activate your account, reset or verify your password, keep records, enable your interactions with other members, address your support requests and occasionally, reach out to you. It assists us to create and enhance our services, to evaluate and monitor the performance ourselves as well as your preferences and performance and to optimize and individualize our service and improve your experience (for example, by providing recommendations of suitable Gigs, ranking search results, etc.).\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">To safeguard the market and minimize the fraudulent cases and also to make the market safe and secure for the services. For instance, we employ personal information to fight against unlawful, fraudulent, and improper activities, control the content’s quality, investigate security issues and risks, confirm or verify the information you provide, investigate the reports and complaints regarding users, enforce the Terms of Service, and follow the laws. To meet the above objectives, we perform some behavioral analytics and in some instances if there is activity that we deem to be detrimental to the Owrners marketplace, other users, our community or third parties, then some functionality of Owrners may be restricted or limited. If you wish to contest any such decision, kindly write to us at privacy@Owrners.com.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">To communicate with you, pursuant to your express communications to us or as otherwise authorized by you or as provided for herein under this Policy.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">To inform and publicize the Site, our services and the Owrners marketplace. For instance, with the data you provide to us we use it to send direct marketing communication (as described below), to display information that may interest you, to coordinate and administer referral programs, competitions or other promotional activities or events.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">for the purpose of keeping proper records of the business, for the purpose of responding to legal demands by public authorities and for the purpose of being able to adhere to the laws and regulations.\r\n </font></li></ul><div><font color=\"#374151\">In case we want to use the information for a purpose other than those stated herein, we shall seek your permission.\r\n </font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\"><b>Direct marketing:\r\n </b></font></div><ul><li><font color=\"#374151\">We also use your personal information to communicate direct marketing over the products, services or promotions of Owrners or related services which we believe may be of interest to you. This could be through the use of e-mail, mail, mobile phone messaging, and telephone or even through adverts on the internet.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">Whenever we process your personal information for marketing purposes, the legal basis for this processing is our legitimate interest, your consent or other legal grounds provided by the local legislation. You have a right to opt out of direct marketing, of any type, at any time – this can be done by following the link provided in any of the communications or by emailing optout@Owrners.com.\r\n </font></li><li><font color=\"#374151\">We try to avoid making direct marketing to a reasonable and proportionate level and send you the communications which we think may be of interest or relevance to you according to the information we have.\r\n </font></li></ul><div><font color=\"#374151\">This Site also uses reCAPTCHA to protect it. Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service are relevant with regard to data that is collected through reCAPTCHA. Google reCAPTCHA has to be applied in order to avoid frauds and misuse of the Site by means of using automated machines. For further information please click on Google’s privacy policy.\r\n </font></div><div><font color=\"#374151\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>5. How Long Do We Keep Personal Information?</b></span></font></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">﻿In general, we retain personal information for only as long as is necessary to fulfill the purpose for which the information was obtained. Nevertheless, in some cases, we will process your personal information for a longer period than mentioned above. We will retain personal information for the following purposes:</span></div><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); display: inline !important;\">As long as it is reasonable and has a connection with our business, for instance, to have a record of your transactions with us in case of disputes or disagreements;</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span>with respect to personal information from closed accounts in order to meet the requirements of the laws, prevent frauds, collect any amount due and payable, handling of disputes and problems, assist any investigation, exercise of rights to our Site terms and other legal actions;</li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">to fulfill statutory or other requirements to which Owrners is bound to; and\r\n </span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">It is necessary to use it, if and to the extent, the need arises in order to preserve the evidence within statutes of limitation.</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>6. Children</b></span>\r\n </span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">This Site is provided to, and may only be used by users who are at least eighteen (18) years old and/or are otherwise legally capable of forming a binding contract. Users under 18 and above 13 years are allowed to use the Site only if they have a parent’s or a legal guardian’s permission and if the account belongs to the parent or the legal guardian. Persons under the age of 13 may not use the Site or the Owners services. We do not intentionally gather personal information from children under 13 years of age. Parents and guardians should always monitor their children’s activities. In the event that we find out that we have collected or received personal information from a child less than 13 years of age, we will erase that information. If you think we may have information from or about a child less than 13 years old, please let us know at privacy@Owrners.com.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>7. Sharing Personal Information with Third Parties\r\n </b></span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n </span></p><p>We share your personal information with third parties as detailed below:\r\n </p><ul><li><b>With other users and Site visitors.</b> Upon registration, your username, the country you live in, and other information concerning your activity on the Site becomes open to all the users of the Site. Such information may include photos you upload, your published portfolio, Gig information, ratings and reviews and any other information that you want to provide on your profile. We also give you the opportunity to share and contribute content through posts, comments and in other public areas such as forums, blogs, etc. Bear in mind that some information like user name and profile information along with the content that you post will be available for public viewing when you engage in the use of such features. If you were verified as a business seller (trader) on Owrners, some of the information will be considered as provided in accordance with the applicable legal requirements to the Pakistan buyers that may include your name, address, email, phone, and business registration number, as well as your self-certification to Owrners’ policies and applicable norms. Your information will also be exchanged with other users when you chat or otherwise communicate with them. To this extent, information and/or data that you make available to other Owrners users is made available at your own risk. If you decide to provide other users, including Sellers providing you a service via Owrners, your personal information, such personal information will be shared with other users as separate controllers. Although in our Terms Of Service we require Sellers to maintain the information shared with them confidential, Owners cannot guarantee that all users would do the same and it is your responsibility to make sure other users would adhere to your standards;\r\n </li><li><b>With users with whom you interact.</b> This is what we do with personal information so that we can be able to enable more interactions between users. For instance, if you are a Buyer, we may share some information about you, like the fact that this is your first order with Owrners, with the Seller to make sure that the Seller’s services will meet your needs; this is done sparingly and only in the interest of the Seller and yourself;\r\n </li><li><b>With Service Providers.</b> We disclose personal information for the following business purposes with service providers that offer us services for the operation of the Site, for the opening and operation of your account and for offering complementary services and solutions: These are; Hosting services, Billing and Payment processors and vendors, Fraud detection and prevention services, CRM systems, Forum hosting, Community management services, Data and Cyber security services, Web analytics and performance tools, Translation tools, IT SaaS services, Session recording services, Communication systems, Mailing systems, Data optimization and marketing services, Data enrichment services, Legal and financial consultants and technical consultants. As required by the legal regulation, we use the necessary technical and organizational measures to ensure that the third parties will also protect the personal information and process it in compliance with our requirements;\r\n </li><li>For instance, when you file a report or a complaint against a user. When you make reports or complaints against other users or provide other information we require protecting their rights or in connection with legal processes we may share your personal information.\r\n </li><li><b>For legal reasons. </b>Personal information is disclosed to law enforcement agencies, public authorities or any other third party for subpoena or court order, judicial process, to regulatory authorities if we believe that the law requires it or it is reasonably necessary for compliance with the law; where we believe that disclosure is appropriate to investigate actual or suspected violation of law, security breach, breaches of this Policy; to respond to claims; and to protect the rights, property or personal safety of Owrners;\r\n </li><li><b>For payments and fraud detection.</b> Personal information is disclosed to payment processors, fraud detection agencies and similar third parties to enable payment made through the Site, to safeguard the Site and to protect it against fraud, unauthorized transactions (including money laundering), claims and other legal liabilities;\r\n </li><li><b>With social media partners.</b> Our Site has some interactive tools which are linked to social networks, including the use of single sign on. We also disclose certain personal information to such social media platforms or marketing partners including Facebook and Google in order to advertise our services or the Owrners marketplace. Some features and the third party services used on such sites collect some information about you and may set a cookie to make such features work. Features of such third parties are controlled by their policies;\r\n </li><li><b>With our corporate affiliates.</b> We disclose personal information to Owrners corporate affiliates to conduct our and our affiliates’ business, to provide additional services for you, to prevent frauds and to ensure security of the services, to market our and our affiliates’ services and for other purposes stated above; and\r\n </li><li><b>In the context of a corporate transaction.</b> Personal information will also be disclosed where Owrners is involved in a business transition, for example, a merger, acquisition or sale of all or part of its assets, bankruptcy or other similar circumstances. If for example we sell any business or assets we will make your data available to the buyer. In the event that we sell our company or a majority of our assets are sold to a third party, the information we have collected pertaining to our users will be considered as transferred assets.\r\n </li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>8. Where We Process Your Personal Information</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Some of the personal information you provide to us will be stored or processed on our behalf by third party suppliers and data processors</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">﻿</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> and may be located in other jurisdiction like United States where laws are different from your country of residence. There are also disclosures to third parties and internally, whereby personal information is transferred from one country Area to countries that do not meet the adequacy standard as recognized by the data protection laws. Regarding data transfers to such recipients we ensure the appropriate safeguards are in place of standard contractual clauses as amended from time to time and/or other similar means. We will use all reasonable efforts to safeguard your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, use or alteration.</span>\r\n </p><p><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">9. Cookies</span>\r\n </b></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">we employ cookies and similar technologies including web beacons, pixels, tags and scripts for various purposes to enhance your experience, to provide our services</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">to measure the performance of the website and for marketing. This Policy applies where our Site uses cookies to process your personal information. The types of cookies used by us and our partners in connection with the Site and our service are divided into the categories of essential cookies, analytics cookies and marketing cookies.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">F</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">or more information about how we and our third party service providers use cookies and your ability to control these Cookies,please visit our Cookie Policy</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">.</span>\r\n </p><p>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>10. Do Not Track</b></span>\r\n </span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Do Not Track (DNT) is a privacy preference that can be enabled by users in several web browsers, thus enabling users to decline being tracked on the internet by websites and other services. We do not respond to browser requests that ask not to be tracked online, also known as ‘Do Not Track’, but our Cookie Policy explains how you can turn off cookies.</span>\r\n </span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\r\n </span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>11. External Links</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please remember however that the Site may contain links to third party sites and if you navigate to a third party site from the Site any information you provide to that site and any use which that third party may make of it are not governed by this Policy. You should read the privacy statement of each site that you visit. This Policy only relates to personal information collected through our Site. If you upload content, including personal information, to a social network and then tag the Site, your submission will be subject to that social network’s terms of use and privacy policy, even where you post on an official Owrners page on the social network. These terms of use and privacy policies are not under our control and we have not assessed the adequacy of the same. You should therefore go through these before you feed the site with any personal information.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>12. Security</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">In an effort to ensure the security of the Site, our services and personal information and in order to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, loss, misuse, alteration, destruction or damage to it, we use technical and organizational measures that correspond to industry standards and internal procedures. Among other things, we maintain on a regular basis a PCI DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standards) certification (where applicable) in connection with payment by credit cards. Furthermore, we make sure that through legal means the third party that processes your personal information ensures the confidentiality and the integrity of your data in a secure manner. However, the data transmitted through the internet is not fully secure and we shall make our best effort to protect your personal information but you acknowledge that the transmission of data through the internet to the Site is not fully protected. After that, we will make every possible effort in order to ensure that your data is not accessible to unauthorized persons, using strict procedures and security features.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: var(--light-color); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); display: inline !important; font-size: 14px;\">The users who have registered to the Site have agreed not to disclose their password to any third party and keep it a secret.</span><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Additional details on measures that have been taken to ensure data security can be availed on request.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>13. Specific Provisions for EU, EEA and UK Users</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">This section of the Policy applies to you if you are located in the EU, EEA or UK.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The Controller (within the meaning of the EU and UK General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”)) for the processing of person</span>al data as descri<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">bed in this Privacy policy is: Owrners Ltd., add address Pakistan.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Under applicable regulation, you have the following rights in respect of your personal information:</span>\r\n </p><ul><li>to receive information about how and on what basis your personal information is processed and to receive a copy;\r\n </li><li>to correct personal information that have been provided in the wrong manner;\r\n </li><li>in order to delete your personal information in the following cases: (a) where you no longer believe that we have a legitimate reason to process your personal information; (b) where we are processing your personal information based on our or a third party’s legitimate interests and you object to such processing and we are unable to demonstrate that we have compelling legitimate interests in continuing the processing; (c) where you provided your personal information to us and believe it is unlawfully used without consent;\r\n </li><li>to restrict processing of your personal information where: (a) the accuracy of the personal information is disputed; (b) the processing is unlawful but the individual does not consent to the erasure of the personal information; (c) we no longer need the personal information for the purposes it was collected for but it is required for the exercise of legal claims or (d) the individual has objected to the processing of the personal information for the purposes of legitimate interest;\r\n </li><li>to refuse to be subjected to measures which are based on automated processing or profiling;\r\n </li><li>where you have given us your information with your consent, to request from us a copy of this data in a commonly used and machine readable format and to ask us to transfer (port) this data to another data controller; or\r\n </li><li>To request a copy of or to access to the safeguards that is used to transfer your personal information.\r\n </li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><b>In specific situations you have the right to receive, on grounds relating to your particular situation, the processing of your personal data by us and we can no longer process your personal data. Furthermore, where your personal data is used for direct marketing purposes, you have the right to object to the processing of personal data relating to you for direct marketing including profiling that takes place in relation to such direct marketing. In this case your personal data will no longer be processed for such purposes by us.</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please contact us as stated in the “Contact Us” section in order to exercise your rights.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Besides the above, you have the right to bring an action against an organization or a controller before a court of competent jurisdiction for breach of data protection. It is important to note that the right of access and the right to erasure are relative rights and the interest of other persons may prevent you from exercising your right of access or erase in compliance with the local laws.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">When you request information from us, we may ask that you provide additional data for the purpose of confirming your identity and security prior to disclosing said information. The fee may be assessed to the extent allowed by law. We will not process requests that are frivolous, jeopardize the privacy of others, or are extremely impractical. Subject to applicable laws, we may also retain certain personal information for longer periods (known as the retention period) where required for legal or compliance purpose.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>14. Specific Provisions for US Residents</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">This section of the Policy applies to you, if you are a US resident based on your residency and except as specified otherwise.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Personal information we collected from users, for the Proceeding Twelve (12) Months, have the following categories:</span>\r\n </p><ul><li>Data you decided to upload or otherwise give to Owrners may include the following types of information: (i) identifiers and personal information, such as your name, your physical postal address, your online identifiers, your email address, your passport number or driving license number, and your social security number; (ii) protected classifications, such as gender; facial image; audio, electronic, or similar information; (iii) professional or employment-related information; (iv) educational information; (v) commercial information; (vi) any audio and other sensory information you choose to provide, such as if you use audio in services provided on Owrners.\r\n </li><li>When you use Owrners, we collect various kinds of information that you provide or that we are able to obtain. These data include (i) identifiers and personal information, such as your name and contact information and your online identifiers; (ii) demographic information; (iii) commercial information, including records of products or services purchased or considered; (iv) your activity information, like log-in and log-out times and session durations; (v) your interaction with and use of the service; and (vi) location information.\r\n </li><li>We collect or receive information from third parties like service providers, advertisers, and accounts you link to Owrners. This includes: (i) Identifiers and personal information such as your name, online identifiers, email addresses, internet protocol (IP) addresses, and information about the devices you use to access our services (e.g., your browser type, version, and time zone setting); (ii) Professional or employment-related information; (iii) Internet or electronic network activity information; (iv) Commercial information; and (v) Location information.\r\n </li><li>Inferences derived from all the information mentioned earlier are used to form a profile about you.\r\n </li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The identifiable personal information we gather or obtain is used for the business objectives or purposes we outlined earlier, under the section titled \"How Do We Use the Information Collected?”.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We may share each of the categories listed with third-parties whom we engage as partners so they can assist us and you benefit from their services, such sharing is further explained in our Privacy Policy under “Sharing Personal Information with Third Parties”. Over the last 12 (twelve) months, we have disclosed any and all of the categories listed above for business purposes.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We never sell your information for monetary compensation, but we may share certain identifiable data with our advertising partners to fulfill Owner\'s personalized ad and content recommendations needs when you engage a page within the Site. This activity may include selling and sharing of personal information by certain US state privacy laws. You may also opt out of using or disclosing your personal data for such Targeted advertising. All you have to do is go to our Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information part to apply your right. However, it is to be noted that even if you opt out of the targeted advertising, you will continue to see the generalized Owrners ads.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You are entitled to the following rights subject to certain exceptions, in relation to personal information related to you:</span> \r\n </p><ul><li>You have a right to request access to the personal information we have collected about you over the past 12 months, including: The following is a list of the categories of personal information that we have collected about you: (i) the categories of personal information collected; (ii) the categories of sources from which the personal information is collected; (iii) the business or commercial purpose for collecting the personal information; (iv) the categories of third parties with whom the personal information was shared; and (v) the specific pieces of personal information collected about you.\r\n </li><li>You have the right to request to obtain your personal information that is related to you which we have obtained from you under certain conditions and exemptions.\r\n </li><li>You also have the right to rectify the personal information you have provided to us.\r\n </li><li>You have the right to opt-out of the sale of personal information.\r\n </li><li>You have a right to opt out of targeted advertisement. \r\n </li><li>You also have a right not to be discriminated against for exercising your rights.\r\n </li><li>You also have a right to submit the request through an agent. If you use an authorized agent to submit a request to access or delete your personal information on your behalf, the authorized agent must: The essential requirements for a third party to have a valid proxy include; (1) the third party should be registered to do business in the relevant Secretary of State; (2) the third party should sign an affidavit of registration; (3) the third party should submit other documents or proof of authority to act on your behalf. We may also need to ask you for some information directly from you, and directly ask you whether you have authorized the agent to make the request.\r\n </li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">To make such requests, it is our request that you open a Customer Relations ticket. If you do not have an Active Owrners account, please feel free to write to us at privacy@Owrners.com.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">For all Owrners Workspace users, please contact us at workspace-support@Owrners.com.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We will ensure you validate your request through the details that are attached to your account such as the email address. ID may also be needed to be produced such as government identification.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>15. Updating Personal Information</b></span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We implement measures to ensure that the personal information we gather is correct and updated and also give you a chance to modify the data you provided through your account settings. Should you have any reason to believe that your information is in any way incorrect or inaccurate please inform us at once. We will ensure that where it is necessary or possible we investigate the matter and promptly correct any inaccuracy as soon as possible where necessary or provide you with how you can easily update it or delete it–where we do not have to retain the information for legitimate business or legal reasons. When you make a request to change some data in your personal information, you will be required to provide some identification to enable us to process your request. If for any reason you have a problem with deleting your personal information, please contact Owrners’ Customer Support and we will make reasonable efforts to delete any such information subject to any privacy laws.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Users can view and edit the personal information provided by them by going to the account profile page on the Site.</span>\r\n </p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you remove your User Generated Content (“UGC”) as defined in the Owrners Terms of Service from the Site, your UGC may still be seen in cache an