on: ; --tw-ordinal: ; --tw-slashed-zero: ; --tw-numeric-figure: ; --tw-numeric-spacing: ; --tw-numeric-fraction: ; --tw-ring-inset: ; --tw-ring-offset-width: 0px; --tw-ring-offset-color: #fff; --tw-ring-color: rgba(69,89,164,.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow: 0 0 transparent; --tw-ring-shadow: 0 0 transparent; --tw-shadow: 0 0 transparent; --tw-shadow-colored: 0 0 transparent; --tw-blur: ; --tw-brightness: ; --tw-contrast: ; --tw-grayscale: ; --tw-hue-rotate: ; --tw-invert: ; --tw-saturate: ; --tw-sepia: ; --tw-drop-shadow: ; --tw-backdrop-blur: ; --tw-backdrop-brightness: ; --tw-backdrop-contrast: ; --tw-backdrop-grayscale: ; --tw-backdrop-hue-rotate: ; --tw-backdrop-invert: ; --tw-backdrop-opacity: ; --tw-backdrop-saturate: ; --tw-backdrop-sepia: ; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(55, 65, 81); font-family: Söhne, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \"Noto Sans\", sans-serif, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\", \"Noto Color Emoji\"; white-space-collapse: preserve; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);\">This sample is meant to be inspirational and should be customized to align with the specific brand voice, value proposition, and unique selling points of your freelancing website.</p>','on','normal_layout','none','on',NULL,'01','all',1,'2023-11-02 06:43:42','2023-11-19 07:42:47'),(9,'Terms Conditions','terms-conditions','<b><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Owrners\'s Terms of Service</span>\r\n </b><div><b>Last update: July 2024\r\n </b></div><div>The following Terms of Service (these “Terms of Service”) apply to any use of the Owrners website and/or the Owrners mobile application, including any content, functionality and services made available through www.Owrners.com or the Owrners mobile application (the \"Site\") by Owrners International Ltd. (add address). Owrners International Ltd. Is referred hereto as “Owrners” “we” or “us” and “you” or “user” means you as an user of the Site.\r\n </div><div>Before using the Site, please, read the Terms of Service very attentively. You understand and accept that by accessing the Site, registering an account or by clicking ‘I agree’ or similar language when such feature is made available to you, you are agreeing to be bound by these Terms of Service, Owrners Payment Terms, Owrners Community Standards, as well as any other standards, conditions, policies, guidelines, and in-product disclosures (hereinafter collectively referred to as the “Terms”). You further agree, you have read and understood our Privacy Policy, which is listed here. If you do not wish to accept these Terms or the Privacy Policy you are advised not to use the Site. For more elaborated policies concerning the activity and usage on the Site, please refer to the specific articles of the present text.\r\n </div><div>Please do not hesitate to contact our Customer Support team at any time for any questions you may have concerning the Site or the Terms. It can be noted that contacting our Customer Support team can be done by filling out the request here. Please see here for further details on the contact points that we have established.\r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">1. Representations and Warranties</span>\r\n </b></div><div>This Site is provided and made available only to users who are over the age of eighteen (18) and of legal age to enter legally binding contracts. If you are a person under the age of 18 and above 13 years of age, then you are allowed to use the Site only through an account owned by a parent or legal guardian with their consent. If you are under 13 years of age, you are not allowed to use the Site or the Owrners services. \r\n </div><div>Subject to the terms set forth herein, you may use the Site if you satisfy all of the foregoing requirements. If you do not satisfy all of these conditions you must not use or attempt to use the Site.\r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">2. Key Terms</span>\r\n </b></div><div>Consumers are customers who hire services on Owrners.\r\n </div><div>Custom Offers are special offers that a Seller can make in relation to the need of a Buyer.\r\n </div><ol><li><b>Gig® Extras</b> are features that the Seller provides over and above the main Gig at an extra cost that is set by the Seller.\r\n </li></ol><div><b>Gig® Packages </b>enable Sellers to list services in various options and prices. It also allows for packages that can have additions such as upgrades that enable Sellers to set the price of their service to be more than pkr (add amount) for the basic package.​\r\n </div><div><b>Gig® Page</b> is where the Seller can describe what he or she is offering in the Gig and the terms of the Gig and the Buyer can order the Gig and make an Order.\r\n </div><div><b>Gig® / Gigs® / Services</b> are the products that are sold in Owrners platform.\r\n </div><div><b>Hourly Contract</b> means an Order based on an hourly Custom Offer with an Hourly Rate.\r\n </div><div><b>Hourly Limit / Weekly Hourly Limit</b> is a term which refers to the working hours per week stated in an Hourly Contract.\r\n </div><div><b>Hourly Rate</b> means the rate per hour agreed between Seller and Buyer for an Hourly Contract.\r\n </div><div><b>Hourly Weekly Report / Weekly Report Report</b> refer to the working hours declared by Seller in a weekly basis in relation to an Hourly Contract.\r\n </div><div><b>Logo Design</b> is an original design for a logo which is created by a Seller using Owrners Logo Maker tool.\r\n </div><div><b>Logo Maker </b>is the AI-Logo Design tool provided by Owrners to its users as elaborated in these Terms of Service.\r\n </div><div><b>Order Page</b> Order Page is a section of a website where Buyers and Sellers interact with each other concerning an ordered Service.\r\n </div><div><b>Orders</b> Orders are legal contracts between a Buyer and Seller.\r\n </div><div><b>Professions </b>are where eligible Sellers can advertise the Services that they provide on Owrners depending on the skills.\r\n </div><div><b>Sellers</b> or <b>Freelancers </b>refers to the users who list and deliver Services on Owrners platform.\r\n </div><div><b>Seller Page</b> Seller Page is the place where Sellers can provide all the information they want, show other works they done, Professions and anything that might be useful for Buyers\r\n </div><div> \r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">3. Overview (Main terms, in a nutshell)</span>\r\n </b></div><ul><li>Owrners has its own rules and only the registered users are allowed to purchase and sell on the website. When creating an account, you undertake to provide us with any business or personal information that is accurate, complete and updated and notify us immediately of any changes to such information. Further, you cannot register an account for any improper use or with a view to give false information. By using the Site, you agree that you are solely responsible for any and all activity that occurs on your account and that you will not share your password with anyone and that you will ensure that your password is kept secure. We shall not be held responsible for any act or omission that you undertake in relation to your account.\r\n </li><li>Pricing is set by the sellers; they do not require any approval from anyone. The services that are listed in the Owrners can be provided at a base price of Pkr (add amount) and the minimum Hourly Rate must not be less than Pkr (add amount). Owrners is also free to set a higher base price for starting in specific categories.\r\n </li><li>Consumers on Owrners pay for an Order upfront, as explained further on the Payment tab. In Hourly Contracts, Owrners Pro Clients pay once a week, every Monday for the hours that are stated in the Hourly Weekly Report (For details, please refer to the Hourly Contract on Payment Terms).\r\n </li><li>Regarding fees and payments please read the Payment Terms.\r\n </li><li>Sellers must Honor their Orders and may not cancel Orders frequently or without good reason. Cancelling Orders will impact Sellers’ credibility and rank.\r\n </li><li>Sellers are awarded account levels for the performance of the various metrics. For more information about it, you can read on the Levels section below.\r\n </li><li>Any form of payment other than placing an Order through the Site is prohibited by the Users and prohibited by Owrners.com.\r\n </li><li>In Owrners buying process, Buyers get all the ownership rights to the work completed for them, unless there is a provision made by the Seller in their Gig description or if the two parties negotiate on the issue. Note: The Gigs can also have extra costs for Commercial Use License which is indicated under Gig Extras. For more information please visit our “Ownership” and “Commercial Use License” parts below.\r\n </li><li>Owrners is entitled to use all the delivered work that the user agreed to be published as part of the review and Logo Designs for Owrners marketing and promotional related uses.\r\n </li><li>Your privacy is important to us. If you wish to read the Privacy Policy you can do it here.\r\n </li><li>On Owrners, there is the Logo Maker which enables some of the Sellers to provide the Buyers with several unique logo designs which the Buyers can then modify to suit their taste and needs using the Logo Maker tools. Using the Logo Maker, Buyers acquire the full commercial use of the Logo Design with their brand name imprinted on it.\r\n </li><li>&nbsp;If you are a business client using Owrners Pro (“Pro Client”), Owrners Pro Marketplace for businesses with handpicked freelance talent, please see Owrners Pro Terms of Services here.\r\n </li></ul><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">4. Sellers</span>\r\n </b></div><div><b>4.1 Basics\r\n </b></div><div>Sellers use Owrners to post Gigs so that Buyers can access and acquire their services.\r\n </div><div>Sellers may also propose to Buyers other conditions in a separate Custom Offers section besides the Gigs. Custom Offers on an hourly basis may also be offered to the eligible Pro Clients by the Eligible Sellers as follows.\r\n </div><div>Every Gig that you sell and successfully deliver earns your account revenue of 80% of the purchase price. For Hourly Contracts, the Services described in a Weekly Report that was successfully completed, credits your account with a revenue equivalent to 80% of the Hourly Rate for the hours stated in the Weekly Report.\r\n </div><div>Owrners pays Sellers once an Order, or for Hourly Contracts – Hourly Weekly Report, is done. Please refer to our “Orders” section below for further details.\r\n </div><div>To know more about payments, fee and taxes please refer Payment Terms.\r\n </div><div>A seller cannot advertise any of his/her Gigs, Seller Page or any Owrners content through Google Adwords.\r\n </div><div>The Seller’s rating is the average of the reviews made by the Buyers or Pro Account Team Members (in case of Owrners Pro). High ratings enable Sellers to achieve higher Seller levels in the platform. In some cases, the scores may be extremely low, and this will result in the Seller’s account being deactivated (see Levels section below).\r\n </div><div>Sellers are to provide general liability insurance policy that should ensure all the risks that may be associated with the performance of the services.\r\n </div><div>If you declare yourself to sell on Owrners for purposes relating to your primary job or profession, you will be considered as a “Business Seller” and the following additional term will apply to you: Business Sellers, will, upon the creation of a Gig, or as requested by Owrners, provide the following information and documents: (a) Name, telephone number, address and email address; (b) Photocopy of identification card/Passport or any other electronic identification as we may require; (c) Payment details; (d) Trade registration number or any other identification number and the trade register in which the Business Seller is registered in case the business seller is registered; (e) A statement from the Business seller which ensures that he or she will only offer products or services that are compliant with the European Union’s applicable laws; and (f)Any further documents that support the information provided. (ii) If a Business Seller doesn’t provide this information and documents within a given reasonable period of time, Owrners may limit or terminate the account.\r\n </div><div><b>4.2 Gigs®\r\n </b></div><div>Sellers are permitted to have only a certain number of active Gigs depending on their level status as explained below.\r\n </div><ul><li>Services offered on Owrners platform are User Generated Content.\r\n </li><li>Gigs and/or users may be removed by Owrners from the Site for violations of the Terms, which may include (but are not limited to) the following violations and/or materials:\r\n </li><li>Gigs and/or users may be removed by Owrners from the Site for violations of the Terms, which may include (but are not limited to) the following violations and/or materials:\r\n <ul><li>Unauthorized or bogus services.\r\n </li><li>Copyright Infringement, trademark infringement, and violation of a third party’s terms of service to be filed through the Intellectual Property Claims Policy outlined here\r\n </li><li>Adult oriented services, pornographic, inappropriate/obscene\r\n </li><li>Imitations of Gigs made with purpose\r\n </li><li>Spam, nonsense, violence or deception related Gigs\r\n </li><li>Gigs as a misrepresentation to the Buyers or others\r\n </li><li>This means that one is allowed to resell only certain goods, and not all of them that he or she has purchased.\r\n </li><li>Providing to write academic works for Buyers\r\n </li><li>Service or delivery that is of low quality\r\n </li><li>Marketing Owrners and/or Owrners Gigs through actions that are forbidden by any laws, regulations, and/or by third parties’ terms of service, as well as through any marketing that might harm our relations with users or partners.\r\n </li><li>Any gigs that are pulled due to violation of the above stated reasons may lead to the termination of the Seller’s account.\r\n </li><li>Gigs that were deleted for violation cannot be restored or edited in any way, shape or form.\r\n </li><li>Gigs may be taken down from our listings based on Terms of Service, low rating, and/or users’ misconduct.\r\n </li></ul></li><li>Gigs may include URLs to pre-approval of URL patterns within the Gig description and requirements box. Websites containing gig promoting contents which are prohibited by Owrners’ policy will be pulled down.\r\n </li><li>For gigs, there has to be a Gig image that has to do with the service provided. Freelancers must provide service that is as good as the images used in the creation of their Gig. Repeated delivery that does not meet quality displayed on the Gig images may cause Seller to lose Seller level or the account to be terminated.\r\n </li><li>Gigs may include an approved Gig video that is uploaded through the Gig management tools provided by Owrners as elaborated on here.\r\n </li><li>Any information provided on the Gig Page that negates or goes around these Terms is not allowed.\r\n </li><li>Gigs which meet the requirements may create Gig Packages to present their services in formats with different prices for the chosen Gig.\r\n </li><li>Some categories are exclusive to Pro Freelancers to be able to create Gigs. If you are not a Pro Freelancer, creating a Gig for services that are available for Pro Freelancers only will lead to deletion of your Gig.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>4.3 Gig® Extras\r\n </b></div><ul><li>Gig Extras are additional services that a Buyer may add to the Seller’s Gig and which cost extra amount that the Seller sets.\r\n </li><li>&nbsp;In violation of Terms Gig Extras may be removed. For specific terms, please refer to the Gigs section in this page for a list of prohibited services under the Terms. Gigs can be deleted because of the violations that are discovered in the Gig Extras.\r\n </li><li>Gig Extras must be services that are in some way connected with the base service and are to be delivered as part of the Order.\r\n </li><li>Gig Extras might encompass different forms of services that are parts to a higher quality delivered service.\r\n </li><li>Sellers are allowed to prolong the time of an Order in case if one or several Gig Extras are added to the Order. This is to ensure that the amount of time spent on the extra service is well catered for.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>4.4 Levels\r\n </b></div><div>Our level system helps Sellers to be equipped with numbers that show what contributes to their advancement. Sellers will be qualified for the new benefits and tools that will be introduced when they are more experienced and belong to higher Level.\r\n </div><ul><li>Owrners Sellers can get account levels by their activity and performance statistics. Top Rated Seller Level (TRS) program is also rated manually and therefore, eligibility is attained. Information concerning the level criteria and the performance measures can be accessed from the following links here.\r\n </li><li>In the course of the TRS evaluation some categories of sellers may be asked to sit for tests or undergo other verification procedures.\r\n </li><li>The level criteria as well as the benefits and tools associated with each level may be modified by Owrners at any given time.\r\n </li><li>Failure to adhere to these Terms, may lead to your account being locked from leveling up in the leveling system, your account being barred from the leveling system and/or your account being deprived of certain privileges and/or benefits.  \r\n </li></ul><div><b>4.5 Pro Freelancers\r\n </b></div><ul><li>Pro freelancers on the other hand are those freelancers who are hand selected and vetted by Owrners. Applying for Owrners Pro is open to everyone: new and existing Freelancers with special emphasis.\r\n </li><li>Pro Freelancers’ eligibility is always reviewed by Owrners to make sure that the set quality standards and expectations of the Pro Freelancer selection are met. Owrners also has a discretion to alter the entitlement of a Pro Freelancer in consideration to the above evaluation. However, those Freelancers who are not able to provide their high quality service due to a significant decrease in their ratings, constant delay, higher cancellation rate or violating the Terms also lose their Pro Freelancer status and the related privileges.\r\n </li><li>The Pro Freelancers public profile will also be integrated into Owrners Enterprise catalog as a part of Owrners Business Solutions. This is here where Pro Freelancers can decide to opt out of the Owrners Enterprise catalog.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>4.6 Seller Features\r\n </b></div><div>The following are some of the privileges that are enjoyed by the Owrners Sellers in as much as they get to affect how their services are presented in the online marketplace.\r\n </div><div><b>Custom Offer\r\n </b></div><ul><li>Sellers can offer the Buyer Custom Offers that are aimed at meeting certain needs of the Buyer.\r\n </li><li>Custom Offers are set by the Seller providing the details of the service, the price and the time required to complete the service.\r\n </li><li>Custom Offers are initiated from the conversation page.\r\n </li><li>Some of the services offered through Custom Offers may not be against Owrners’ policies as stated in their policies.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>Hourly Contract\r\n </b></div><ul><li>Eligible Sellers may propose to their eligible Pro Clients the Hourly Contracts.\r\n </li><li>The Custom Offer that is to be issued by Seller must contain features of Hourly Rate and estimated number of working hours in the Hourly Contract. The minimum working hours on Hourly Contracts is eight hours.\r\n </li><li>Pro Clients can also request Seller to state an Hourly Limit for working hours per week, and in that regard, Seller must include such information in the hourly Custom Offer. It also means that Pro Client can change the Hourly Limit at any time he wants and the change will be effective right away. In the case that the Seller has already reported working hours for a certain week, the new Hourly Limit cannot exceed the working hours already given by Seller for that week.\r\n </li><li>Either Pro Client or Seller can cancel the Hourly Contract at any time with the prior notice of twenty-four hours on the Hourly Contract Order Page. This is also true for Pro Client in that he can also decide to put on hold the Hourly Contract at any time given a 24 Hrs written notice. Sellers has to declare the working hours and must deliver the work in the said 24 hours prior to the notice period and Pro Client has to pay the required amount on the next weekly billing cycle as mentioned in the Payment Terms.\r\n </li><li>Any Hourly Contract that had no activity during a period of 3 months will be automatically terminated.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>Time reporting:</b> Sellers should report the hours as soon as they have completed the work with enough details explaining the work done by the sellers. This means that once Sellers has logged their working hours it will be forwarded to the client for approval. Sellers are free to input extra details and the files that might be useful to shed more light on the topic. This extra information might be used by Owrners’ Customer Support in case of any confrontation.\r\n </div><ul><li>Sellers opined that hours have to be precise and exhaustive, as far as the real working hours are concerned, all based on the Hourly Contract.\r\n </li><li>Sellers agree and agree to not be paid for any reported hours beyond the Hourly Limit as well as time that is greatly beyond the estimated time.\r\n </li><li>All the working hours worked in a week must be submitted by Sunday, by 11:59 PM UTC. Anything not reported within this deadline will not be included in the Weekly Report and the Seller will not be paid for it.\r\n </li><li>For more information about Hourly Contracts please refer to this link.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>Project Milestones\r\n </b></div><ul><li>If the Gigs and Custom Offers price is Pkr (add amount) the number of project milestones can be as many as six, but each of them must be at least for Pkr (add amount), and the Gig must contain at least two milestones. Every one is paid and done individually in relation to each Gig or Custom Offer description and deadlines.\r\n </li><li>After a particular milestone is provided and accepted, the Buyers can decide to proceed with the Order and pay for the next milestone or cancel the Order. In case Buyer fails to pay for the next milestone within ten days of acceptance of the previous milestones, the Order under the next milestones will not proceed. If no acceptance or request for modification were submitted within 8 days after a milestone was marked as Delivered, then such a milestone will be considered complete, however, all the further milestones will not start.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>Gig Subscription  \r\n </b></div><ul><li>A Seller who qualifies for the Gig Subscription Program may sell a fixed term subscription for a particular Gig. The Gig Subscription term will mean that Seller will provide one Order of the same Gig periodically with a set period between Orders being agreed between the Seller and Buyer.\r\n </li><li>Purchasers can cancel future Orders under the Gig Subscription before the payment for such future Orders is made. In such case, Orders under the Gig Subscription will be terminated as per the particular circumstances. This is accompanied by Owrners’ Order Cancelation policy in the Payments Terms once payment has been made.\r\n </li><li>Sellers can cancel the Gig Subscription up to 10 days to the next consecutive Order. Otherwise, the Order Cancelation policy under the Payments Terms of Owrners will be implemented.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>Stock Media\r\n </b></div><ul><li>Eligible Gigs may use a catalog of licensed images, music and footage clips which is referred to as Stock Media.\r\n </li><li>Sellers get 20% of the fees that are collected for direct charges for Standard License Stock Media. After the acquisition and in case Owrners offers Buyers to upgrade their standard license, the upgraded license does not allow Sellers to earn more in terms of revenue share.\r\n </li><li>Important: It is important to note that each of the selected Stock Media item is licensed for a one time use only. The media item chosen must be used only in the delivered work and must not be re-used or used alone. Sellers are not allowed to provide the Buyer and or any third party with the image in its original format. Moreover, the Stock Media are subject to special license terms that are provided by Shutter stock. For more information on the Stock Media license terms please refer to the following link.\r\n </li><li>Important: If you cancel an Order that includes Stock Media, the license to these Stock Media will be canceled as well and you will not be allowed to use these Stock Media anymore.\r\n </li><li>It is important to understand that Stock Media can be purchased by anybody and the Buyer does not own the material exclusively.\r\n </li><li>Here users can seek help from Owrners’ customer support department.\r\n </li></ul><div><b>4.7 Shipping Physical Deliverables\r\n </b></div><div>Some of the Services on Owrners are tangible (arts and crafts, collectable items, etc.). For such types of Gigs, Sellers may choose to set a shipping pricing factor. The following must apply in case Seller and Buyer agreed on Shipping Physical Deliverables:\r\n </div><ul><li>Gigs that have a shipping pricing factor means that physical products have to be delivered to the Buyers.\r\n </li><li>An expense incurred in shipping that is charged on a Gig only relates to the amount of money that Sellers need to charge Buyers to post physical objects.\r\n </li><li>Important: Buyers who have ordered Gigs that are physical in nature will be asked to input a shipping address.\r\n </li><li>A Seller is under the responsibility of making all shipping arrangements as soon as the Buyer provides the shipping address.\r\n </li><li>Owrners does not take any responsibility for the delivery, shipment, tracking, quality and condition of items or their delivery and shall not be held responsible or liable for any damage or other issues arising from the shipment.\r\n </li><li>A tracking number is a good means of eliminating arguments that may arise due to delivery. When delivering your work, we need you to input the tracking number if available in the Order Page.\r\n </li></ul><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">5. Buyers</span>\r\n </b></div><div><b>5.1 Basics\r\n </b></div><div>You may not provide direct payments to Sellers through payment methods that are not Owrners’ platforms.\r\n </div><div>Owrners, however, reserves the right to use all the works delivered by the user which has been agreed to be included and published as part of the review and Logo Designs for Owrners marketing and promotion.\r\n </div><div>Buyers can ask Seller for a Custom Offer which meets certain conditions of the Buyer. Purchasers may also employ brief features to request for services. Services required on the platform should be an allowed service on the platform. Please click here for list of services that are allowed. They should avoid utilizing such features for any purpose other than to search for services on the Owrners platform.\r\n </div><div>You shall ensure that when placing an Order on Owrners you will use only the legal and legitimate money that is not related to any unlawful or fraudulent activity.\r\n </div><div><b>5.2 Purchasing\r\n </b></div><div>Please check out the Payment Terms for information on payments through the Site or for the fees and taxes.\r\n </div><div>You may not pay Sellers to pay or make payment using any method that is not through the Owrners.com site. If you have been given any offer to pay via other means, you should report it to Customer Support here immediately.\r\n </div><div><b>5.3 Recommendation System\r\n </b></div><div>We provide suggestions to users of content that can be of interest to them in an aim to improve the experience on Owrners. For more about Owrners’ Recommendation System see here.\r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">6. Orders</span>\r\n </b></div><div><b>6.1 Basics\r\n </b></div><div>When payment is received, your Order will be processed. In regard to Hourly Contracts, once the Order Initiation Fee has been charged the Order will be initiated.\r\n </div><div>An Order is considered as Complete, when an Order is shipped and is reported as “Delivered” by the Seller and accepted by the Buyer. An Order will be automatically be marked as “Complete” if none has been accepted and no request for modification has been made within 3 days after the Order was marked as “Delivered”. The Buyer can also extend such period by up to 5 days more.\r\n </div><div>For Hourly Contracts, a Weekly Report will be automatically marked as complete if not disputed within 72 hours after charging the Client’s payment method.\r\n </div><div>A purchase through the Logo Maker is finalized once payment has been made by the Buyer.\r\n </div><div>A milestone (on an Order with milestones) is set to “Complete” when it is completed by the Seller and has been reviewed and accepted by the Buyer. If no acceptance or request for modification was submitted to a milestone that was marked as Delivered within 8 days, then the milestone will automatically be marked as Complete, however, if such event occurs the Order will stop and further milestones will not be initiated. When a milestone is delivered and accepted, Buyers may decide to proceed with the Order and pay for the next or may decide to cancel the Order. If Buyer fails to make payment for the next milestone within a period of 10 days from the date of acceptance of the previous milestones then the Order for the next milestones will not commence. Please, notice that if you decide to stop receiving future milestones, the current ordered milestone will not be canceled.\r\n </div><div>The buyers may opt to buy a Gig Subscription, where available in the Gig Page of the Seller. During Gig Subscription term, new Order of the same Gig will be repeated at an interval agreed between the Seller and Buyer. If you have ordered a Gig Subscription, you also agree with the automatic charging of each Order under the Gig Subscription from your Owrners Balance or your saved payment option, if any. If you have no Owrners Balance or saved payment method, you will be asked to confirm payment before the next Order. If for any reason a payment is not processed or made by Buyer, the Orders under the Gig Subscription will be void. Buyer may also terminate future Orders under the Gig Subscription prior to the payment for the such future Orders being made. After payment has been made, the following policy will apply: Order Cancelation policy under the Payments Terms of Owrners. Kindly remember that Sellers can cancel the subsequent Orders under the Gig Subscription within ten days to the subsequent consecutive Order.\r\n </div><div>Some of the Gigs that provide local services might compel Buyers and Sellers to arrange a face-to-face meeting so that Seller can provide the service. In such cases, users should be aware that Owrners does not control the behavior, conduct, safety, suitability or ability of either Buyers or Sellers. Buyers and Sellers therefore take full responsibility of any risks that may arise out of their meeting and/or use or performance of the local services and Owrners shall not be held liable for any of the services that are to be provided by the Sellers locally. If the service is done on the Buyers’ premise, Buyers are advised to ensure they have adequate insurance policies to cover as the premise owner. Owrners’ Terms continue to apply to Orders completed outside the Owrners Platform (as well as the following prohibited conduct: Unlawful Use, Inappropriate Behavior &amp; Language, and Targeted Abuse).\r\n </div><div><b>6.2 Handling Orders\r\n </b></div><div>When a Buyer places an Order, the Seller receives an email notification along with notifications on the Site if he is logged into his account.\r\n </div><div>Sellers are expected to deliver their orders within the time they provided when posting their Gigs or when making a Custom Offer. Failure to do so will enable the Buyer to cancel an Order when an Order is marked as late and is detrimental to the Seller’s level.\r\n </div><div>In marking the Order as “Deliver, Sellers are required to upload completed files and/or evidence of the work done.\r\n </div><div>Deliver Work button may not be used by Sellers in a way that will allow them to avoid Order rules as stated in these Terms. Clicking the “Deliver Work” button where an Order was not fulfilled may lead to cancellation of that Order after it has been processed, a low rating for the Seller and a warning to the Seller.\r\n </div><div>It is the user’s responsibility to check all the files transferred for viruses and malware. In addition, Owrners will not accept responsibility for the losses which may arise from the use of this site, use of content or files transfer.\r\n </div><div>Customers can click on the ‘Request Revisions’ button which is found on the Order Page when an Order is tagged as Delivered if the delivered papers are not as described on the Seller’s Gig Page or if they do not meet the specifications that were provided to the Seller at the start of the order process.\r\n </div><div><b>6.3 Reviews\r\n </b></div><div>Buyer feedback as an aspect of Owrners rating system is incomplete without considering the Reviews given by the Buyers. For more details on how Owrners review system works, please visit here.\r\n </div><div>It means that the reviews will not be deleted if ther