the notice of the claimed copyright infringement or trademark infringement-please refer to the Intellectual Property Claims Policy that is a part of the Terms and Conditions. Please remember that it is our policy in proper circumstances to suspend and/or cancel multiple infringers’ accounts.\r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">10. Ownership</span>\r\n </b></div><div>Ownership and limitations: When the Buyer purchases a Service on Owrners, unless stated otherwise on the Seller’s Gig page/description or in the Custom Offer, upon delivery of the work and subject to payment, the Seller provides the Buyer with the license to use the work delivered from the Seller as a part of the Service on Owrners and/or as a separate work and the Seller relinquishes all moral rights (to the extent permitted by law) in the work. For this reason, the Seller transfers the copyright in the delivered work to the Buyer by express assignment. All transfer and assignment of intellectual property to the Buyer shall be subject to full payment, and the delivery may not be used if payment is cancelled for any reason. For removal of doubt, in custom created work (such as art work, design work, report generation etc.), the delivered work and its copyright shall be the exclusive property of the Buyer and, upon delivery, the Seller agrees that it thereby, pursuant to the Terms, assigns all right, title and interest in and to the delivered work to the Buyer. Some Gigs (including for custom created work) charge additional payments (through Gig Extras) for a Commercial Use License. This means that if you purchase the Gig for personal use, you will own all rights you require for such use, and will not need the Commercial Use License. If you plan to use it for any fee or other consideration, or for any purpose that is related to business or other venture for profit, you will have to purchase the Commercial Use License as an additional Gig Extra and it will grant you wider rights for your business.\r\n </div><div>For Voice Over Gigs, when the work is delivered, and subject to payment, the Buyer is purchasing basic rights (which means the Buyer is paying a one time fee allowing them to use the work forever and for non-commercial purposes). If you intend to use the Voice Over to promote a product and/or service (with the exception of paid marketing channels), you will need to purchase the Commercial Rights (Buy-Out) through Gig Extra. If you intend to use the Voice Over in radio, television and internet commercials, you will need to purchase the Full Broadcast Rights (Buy-Out) through Gig Extra. For further information on the type of buy-outs, please read below.\r\n </div><div>Furthermore, users (both Buyers and Sellers) agree that unless they explicitly indicate otherwise, the content users voluntarily create/upload to Owrners, including Gig texts, photos, videos, usernames, user photos, user videos and any other information, including the display of delivered work, may be used by Owrners for no consideration for marketing purposes and/or other purpose relevant for the operation and function of the Site.\r\n </div><div><b>10.1 Voice Over Commercial Buy-Out\r\n </b></div><div>When purchasing a Voice Over Service, the Seller grants you a non-commercial, perpetual, exclusive, non-transferable, worldwide license to use the purchased Voice Over. This excludes any commercial use, including radio, television and internet commercial spots.\r\n </div><div>By purchasing a Commercial Rights (Buy-Out) with your Order, in addition to the basic rights, the Seller grants you with a license to use the Voice Over for any commercial promotional and non-broadcast purposes for such period agreed with the Seller (and unless agreed otherwise - in perpetuity). Commercial, promotional and non-broadcast purposes means any business related use for the creation of, or to promote a for-profit product or service (with the exception of paid marketing channels), such as (by way of example): explainer videos posted to company websites, social networks or email campaigns, audiobooks, podcast intros, and strictly excludes any illegal, immoral or defamatory purpose.\r\n </div><div>By purchasing a Full Broadcast Rights (Buy-Out) with your Order, in addition to the Commercial Rights, the Seller grants you with a license for full broadcasting for such period agreed with the Seller (and unless agreed otherwise - in perpetuity). Full Broadcasting includes internet, radio, and TV \"paid channels\", such as (by way of example), television commercials, radio commercials, internet radio, and music/video streaming platforms, and strictly excludes any illegal, immoral or defamatory purpose.\r\n </div><div>This Buy-Out is subject to Owrners\'s Terms. There is no warranty, express or implied, with the purchase of this delivery, including with respect to fitness for a particular purpose. Neither the Seller nor Owrners will be liable for any claims, or incidental, consequential or other damages arising out of this license, the delivery or your use of the delivery.\r\n </div><div><b>10.2 Commercial Use License\r\n </b></div><div>By purchasing a “Commercial Use License” with your Order, the Seller grants you a perpetual, exclusive, non-transferable, worldwide license to use the purchased delivery for Permitted Commercial Purposes. For the avoidance of doubt, the Seller retains all ownership rights. “Permitted Commercial Purposes” means any business related use, such as (by way of example) advertising, promotion, creating web pages, integration into product, software or other business related tools etc., and strictly excludes any illegal, immoral or defamatory purpose. This License is subject to Owrners’s Terms. There is no warranty, express or implied, with the purchase of this delivery, including with respect to fitness for a particular purpose. Neither the Seller nor Owrners will be liable for any claims, or incidental, consequential or other damages arising out of this license, the delivery or your use of the delivery.\r\n </div><div><b>10.3 Stock Media\r\n </b></div><div>For Gigs that offer integration of Stock Media in the delivered work through Gig Extras, the Stock Media license terms, available here, apply. Buyers are granted a license to use the delivered work containing Stock Media in accordance with these terms which outline the permissible uses and restrictions associated with the Stock Media.\r\n </div><div><b>11. Disclaimer of Warranties\r\n </b></div><div>You r use of the site, its content and any services or items obtained through the site is at your own risk. The site, its content and any services or items obtained through the site are provided on an \"as is\" and \"as vailable\" basis, without any warranties of any kind, either express or implied, provided that we have acted with reasonable professional diligence. Neither Owrners nor any person associated with Owrners makes any warranty or representation with respect to the completeness, security, reliability, quality, accuracy or availability of the site.\r\n </div><div>The foregoing does not affect any warranties which cannot be excluded or limited under applicable law.\r\n </div><div><b>12. Machine Translation\r\n </b></div><div>Certain user-generated content on the Site has been translated for your convenience using translation softwares powered by Google. Reasonable efforts have been made to provide an accurate translation, however, no automated translation is perfect nor is it intended to replace human translators. Such translations are provided as a service to users of the Site, and are provided \"as is\". No warranty of any kind, either expressed or implied, is made as to the accuracy, reliability, or correctness of such translations made from English into any other language. Some user-generated content (such as images, videos, Flash, etc.) may not be accurately translated or translated at all due to the limitations of the translation software.\r\n </div><div>Google disclaims all warranties related to the translations, express or implied, including any warranties of accuracy, reliability, and any implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose and noninfringement.\r\n </div><div>The official text is the English version of the Site. Any discrepancies or differences created in the translation are not binding and have no legal effect for compliance or enforcement purposes. If any questions arise related to the accuracy of the information contained in the translated content, please refer to the English version of the content which is the official version.\r\n </div><div>13. Deactivate and Disable Account\r\n </div><div>Owrners has the right to suspend the account permanently or put it on hold because of breach of Terms, including low quality services or deliveries, or any other violation of the Site or services.\r\n </div><div>You can get your account disabled forever if you violate the Owrners’ Terms.\r\n </div><div>Owners with disabled accounts will be prohibited from selling or buying on Owners and some of the related content may be deleted. You can refer to the Terms and more specifically the Content Moderation, Notices and Appeals section to learn about your rights to object the decisions made by Site administrators, or contact our Customer Support team for more details regarding the violation and the status of your account.\r\n </div><div>Users may also opt out of the Services provided by Owrners by deactivating their account from the account settings. If a user deactivates his account, he or she will still have to meet the payment balance due. For more information, see “How to deactivate or permanently delete your account (new tab)”.\r\n </div><div>Any provisions of Terms that concerns the relation between a Seller and a Buyer concerning Orders on Owrners will still be effective even if you have closed your account, or if your access to Owrners has been terminated.\r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">14. Security Features</span>\r\n </b></div><div>Users have an option of enabling the account Security features to avoid any unauthorized use of the account.\r\n </div><div>Users must be allowed to confirm their account ownership via the Customer Support by providing materials to show ownership of the account in question.\r\n </div><div><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">15. General Terms</span>\r\n </b></div><div><b>15.1 Changes to these Terms\r\n </b></div><div>Owrners may amend these Terms at any time and any changes will be posted on this website. When such changes are made, Owrners will upload the new copy of the Terms on the respective page.\r\n </div><div>You agree that if you continue to use Owrners after that date, you accept the Terms as modified. If for any reason you do not wish to accept the changes of the Terms you will have to close down your account. For more information, see “How to deactivate or permanently delete your account (Read more)”\r\n </div><div>Owners may amend these Terms because of modifications in the Site, the Site’s policies, the services and in the normal course of a company’s evolution of a product, alterations in any aspect of the Site’s feature or functionality or in circumstances beyond the reasonable control of the Owners; changes in law and regulation, new technologies and security and fraud risks.\r\n </div><div><b>15.2 Indemnification\r\n </b></div><div>To the fullest extent possible pursuant to applicable law, you agree to defend, indemnify, and hold Owrners harmless, including its officers, directors, or shareholders, employees, affiliates and agents, from and against any and all claims, damages, obligations, losses, liabilities, costs, debt and expenses (including attorneys’ fees) arising from: (1) If you breach any of these Terms or any other Owrners Terms, policies and standards; (2) If you violate any third party’s intellectual property rights, access rights, property and/or privacy rights; or (3) Any other kind of claim that your Gig Page, Seller Page, Services, your profile and/or your use of the Site or Owrners services have caused to a third party; subject to, and provided You agree that Owrners has the right to defend itself in any legal manner it wants even if you are indemnifying Owrners in which case, you must assist Owrners in implementing its strategy.\r\n </div><div><b>15.3 Severability\r\n </b></div><div>In the event that any Term is held to be invalid, unlawful or unenforceable for any reason, the validity, legality, and enforceability of the remaining Terms will remain unaffected. Owrners’s decision to not enforce any of the Terms does not mean that it is waiving its rights to enforce that or any other part of the Terms in the future.\r\n </div><div><b>15.4 Entire Agreement\r\n </b></div><div>The Terms herein set out the entire understanding of the parties with regard to the matters addressed therein and revokes any other agreement relating to the Site or the services.\r\n </div><div><b>15.5 Interpretation\r\n </b></div><div>All headings, captions or section titles appearing in the foregoing document and/or any explanation or summary columns as may be applicable, are for reference only, and shall not in any manner affect or change and/or amend any of the provisions in the Terms or legally bind the parties herein in any way.\r\n </div><div>The terms are drafted in English language. Owrners provide this translation for the convenience of the users only. Should there be any discrepancy between the English version and any translation of the Terms, the English version shall be considered the authoritative version. For consumers only, if you are an inhabitant of EEA, the interpretation more beneficial for the consumer shall apply.\r\n </div><div>\r\n </div><div><br></div>',NULL,'normal_layout','none',NULL,NULL,'01','all',1,'2024-03-10 16:36:03','2024-09-18 11:10:14'),(10,'Home Page Two','home-page-two','<p>Home Page Two</p>','on','normal_layout','none',NULL,NULL,'02','all',1,'2024-06-03 14:26:33','2024-06-12 01:12:18'),(11,'FAQs','faqs','<p>                                                </p><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><b><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">FAQs</span></b></p><p><b>How can I trust sellers? Are there disclosures?\r\n                                                \r\n                                            </b></p><div>Like you, every freelancer has to agree to the Owrners Terms of Service when they access our market place. If you have any other papers that you would like a freelancer to sign (for example, an NDA), you can send it to the freelancer through a message (as a file) before ordering this freelancer. Freelancers are able to agree to your terms or not and sign your documents before going to the next step. You should also remember that any additional agreement should not violate Owners’ Terms of Service.\r\n</div><div><b>How can I trust sellers? Are there disclosures?\r\n</b></div><div><b>Are there any safety measures I need to take with sellers (before and after placing my order)?\r\n</b></div><div>As a rule, our Terms of Service are rather broad and comprehensive (as for confidentiality, for instance), and Owrners retains the payments until the order is done. However, as we will not be able to help you with any issue that may happen off Owrners, please do not expose your personal contact details and refrain from using other channels of communication.\r\n</div><div><b>What should I do if I have issues with a seller mid-order?\r\n</b></div><div>If you are dissatisfied with an order that you have placed, there are several possibilities with which you can opt for. First of all, it is always wiser to try to negotiate the problem with the seller on your own. Quite frequently, the need for more dialogue is all that is required to be met in order for a situation to improve. Every order page also has a resolution center where you can propose a cancelation. But if ever you feel that you’re lost or need some assistance, you can always turn to our Customer Support which is open 24/7. All you need to do is to inform them about your order and they will be willing to assist you by.\r\n</div><div><b>What if I am not satisfied with the seller?\r\n</b></div><div>In the event that you have any problems with a seller due to an order, please do note that there is a 13 days window from the time that an order is marked as complete. At this time, we can do a cancellation for you. After this term is over, the seller is subsequently allowed to take payment for the order, and cancelation will be done based on the cooperation of the seller.\r\n</div><div><br></div>\r\n                                            <p></p>','on','normal_layout','none',NULL,NULL,'01','all',1,'2024-09-18 10:39:37','2024-09-18 10:52:24'),(12,'Intellectual Property Claims Policy','intellectual-property-claims-policy','<p style=\"text-align: center; \"><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">Intellectual Property Claims Policy</span>\r\n</p><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Last updated: September, 2024\r\n</span></p><p><b>REPORTING CLAIMS OF INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY\r\n</b></p><p>The content of Owrners.com is principally derived from User Generated Content (UGC). Owrners does not verify user uploaded/created content for violation of the copyright or other rights. However, if you have any reason to believe that any of the content uploaded by other users violates your copyright or a related exclusive right then you should follow the following procedure. Owrners investigates the reported violation and deals with the content that has been found violating third party rights by either removing it or disabling it.\r\n</p><p>If you ever come across any violation of intellectual property rights in Owrners, there are online reporting tools that can be easily filled by the users where they can include all the necessary information. Learn more on how to report content on Owrners here. Moreover, Owrners also retains other reporting flows for the DMCA notices and counter-notices and trademark infringement via the designated agents as outlined below.\r\n</p><p><b>REPORTING COPYRIGHT CLAIMS UNDER THE US DIGITAL MILLENIUM COPYRIGHT ACT (DMCA)\r\n</b></p><p>If you are reporting under the U.S DMCA, you can use the available online tools or you can send an infringement notice (“Notice”) to Owrners’ designated DMCA agent.\r\n</p><p><b>DMCA NOTICE REQUIREMENTS\r\n</b></p><p>In order to allow us to review your report promptly and effectively, the Notice should include the following:\r\n</p><ul><li>Clarification of your copyrighted work and what is covered by the copyright(s) that you are claiming.\r\n</li><li>Your copyright certificate(s)/designation(s) and the type, for instance, registered or unregistered.\r\n</li><li>The registration number or a photocopy of the registration certificate as an evidence of the ownership of the copyrighted work.\r\n</li><li>A brief account of how our user(s) infringe(s) your copyright(s) is as follows:\r\n</li><li>Specific identification of the items that you claim are infringing on your rights and those which you wish to be removed including the GIG® URL, a link to the deliverable given to a user and so on.\r\n</li><li>Your complete name, your address, your email address and your telephone number.\r\n</li><li>Another statement that you have a belief that use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.\r\n</li><li>A sworn statement that the information given in the notice is to the best of their knowledge true and that you are either an owner of a copyright or an exclusive right that has been infringed or you have been mandated to make the complaint by the owner of the copyright or an exclusive right that has been infringed.\r\n</li><li>The date of the document or the record or the report or the letter and your physical or electronic signature.\r\n</li></ul><p>You can send your Notice to our designated DMCA Claims Agent at:\r\n</p><p>Owrners Ltd.\r\n</p><p>Attention: DMCA Claims Agent\r\n</p><p>Add Address and contact number here\r\n</p><p>Or else you can send the said Notice electronically to DMCA@Owrners.com or by contacting our DMCA Agent through a link here.\r\n</p><p>Please remember that we will inform the user who, in your opinion, infringes your copyright, about the Notice, and give him/her a possibility to reply. When enough evidence of infringement is produced, we are able to delete or freeze the reported contents before the user responds. In situations where the allegedly infringing user submits a proper counter-notice stating that he or she is allowed to post the allegedly infringing material, we may inform you and then restore the content in question. In any of the above situations, we shall follow the provisions of 17 U.S.C Section 512 and other related laws.\r\n</p><p>It is also important to note that should you omit on any of the requirements of section 512(c) (3) of the DMCA, your DMCA Notice may not be effective.\r\n</p><p>You should be especially careful if you do not own the copyright for the material or activity on the Website and you provide information about yourself under Section 512(f) of the DMCA, you may be liable for the damages, including costs and attorneys’ fees.\r\n</p><p><b>DMCA COUNTER-NOTICE REQUIREMENTS\r\n</b></p><p>If you are a copyright owner or an agent thereof, and you believe that content that you own or that you have a right to operate on the site was removed or that your access to the content was disabled by mistake or misidentification, you may submit a counter-notice to us (a “Counter-Notice”) by providing written notification to our DMCA Claims agent (identified above). Pursuant to the DMCA, the Counter-Notice must include substantially the following:\r\n</p><ul><li>The date of the document or the record or the report or the letter and your physical or electronic signature.\r\n</li><li>An identification of the material that has been removed or to which access has been disabled and the location at which the material appeared before they were withdrawn or access was blocked.\r\n</li><li>Sufficient information through which the organization can get in touch with you (including your name, your postal address, telephone number and if you have one, your e-mail address).\r\n</li><li>A statement by you under penalty of perjury that you have a good faith belief that the material identified above was removed or disabled as a result of mistake or mistake made by the person who posted said material.\r\n</li><li>A statement that you will not contest the jurisdiction of the Federal District Court for the judicial district in which your address is located (or if you reside outside the United States for any judicial district in which the Website may be found) and that you will not object to accept service from the person (or an agent of that person) who provided the Website with the complaint at issue.\r\n</li></ul><p>The DMCA enables us to replace the deleted content if the owner of the original DMCA Notice does not take legal proceedings against you within ten business days from the time of receiving the copy of your Counter-Notice. Please be advised that we will immediately terminate any user who has provided us with false information regarding copyright infringement upon receiving a complaint. You should also be aware that if you make a material misrepresentation that material or activity on the Website was removed or disabled by mistake or misidentification, you may be liable for damages (including costs and attorneys’ fees) under Section 512(f) of the DMCA.\r\n</p><p><b>REPORTING TRADEMARK INFRINGEMENT\r\n</b></p><p>It is for this reason that the content of Owrners.com is derived from User Generated Content (UGC). Owrners does not scan the content uploaded/created by the users for violation of the trademark or other rights. However, if you are inclined that any of the content uploaded violates your trademark, then, the following steps should be followed. Owrners investigates reported infringement and either removes or disables content found to be infringing third party trademarks.\r\n</p><p>In order to allow us to review your report promptly and effectively, a trademark infringement notice (\"TM Notice\") should include the following:\r\n</p><p>The details of your trademark and the goods and services that you want to be protected by the trademark.\r\n</p><ul><li>Your trademark registration certificate and a printout from the relevant country’s trademark office records of current status and title of the registration. Or a statement that your mark is unregistered, coupled with a court decision which states that you have the rights to the mark.\r\n</li><li>An explanation of how our user(s) infringe(s) your trademark(s) in a brief manner.\r\n</li><li>Specific identification of the materials that you state are being infringed and that you wish to be eliminated such as the GIG® URL, a link to the delivered item to a user and so on.\r\n</li><li>Your full name, your address, your email address and your phone number.\r\n</li><li>A statement that you have a belief that the use of such material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the owner of the trademark, by his/her authorized agent or by the law.\r\n</li><li>A sworn statement that the information given in the notice is correct and that the person who is filing the notice is the owner of the trademark or his/her attorney.\r\n</li><li>Your electronic/physical signature.\r\n</li></ul><p>You can send your Notice to:\r\n</p><p>Owrners Ltd.\r\n</p><p>Attention: Trademark Complaints\r\n</p><p>Add address and contact number\r\n</p><p>Alternatively you can submit the Notice electronically to trademarkcomplaints@Owrners.com.\r\n</p><p>Please do note that we will give the user who is allegedly infringing your trademark information about the TM Notice and they will be able to reply. If the claimant is able to substantiate his/her allegations of infringement sufficiently, the reported materials are deleted or blocked before the user gets a chance to reply. If the allegedly infringing user has given information to us as to why they are allowed to put the allegedly infringing material up we may inform you and then restore the content removed or disabled. In all such cases we will act as per the provisions of law, which shall be applicable in the given case.\r\n</p><p><b>REPEAT INFRINGERS\r\n</b></p><p>We reserve the right to suspend and/or cancel any user’s account in appropriate circumstances if that user is a repeat infringer.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\n</p>',NULL,'normal_layout',NULL,NULL,NULL,'01','all',1,'2024-09-18 10:52:13','2024-09-18 10:52:13'),(13,'Owrners&amp;#039; Community Standards','owrners-community-standards','<p><span style=\"color: var(--light-color); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); display: inline !important; font-size: 36px;\"><b>Owrners\' Community Standards</b></span><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>Introduction</b></span>\r\n</p><p style=\"line-height: 2;\">We’re building a home for a community that wants to be a part of the solution to how the world collaborates. Today, Owrners connects hundreds of writers, designers, producers, videographers, businesspeople, and professionals of all kinds who leverage it to express themselves and do work they care about. We are motivated by each and every one of the community members. We appreciate their input, opinions, and attitudes: this is what makes Owrners so diverse.</p><p style=\"line-height: 2;\"><br></p><p style=\"line-height: 2;\">\r\n</p><p>In order to protect the rights and dignity of all the users to ensure that nobody feels offended or unsafe, we have established a set of community standards to act as the ethical code of conduct on the platform. It can thus be seen how these standards assist in setting the boundaries on what is allowed in the Owrners community and the marketplace, especially in face-to-face and online interactions. They are not bound by any law but we use them to regulate our platform policies. They mirror our beliefs, perceptions and standards of the society. Our community standards are based on principles which include respect, safety, acceptance, support, and openness to ideas.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>Like the standards that we have in our community, these standards are also dynamic and will only become bigger and better. Thus, we have integrated such examples in the community standards for unwanted behaviors in Owrners. Please note that the following is not meant to be exhaustive but rather illustrative of what may be done.\r\n</p><p>We want our community to report anything that is not okay using the tools we provide to them. It is our goal to provide the best experience for all community members and as such please adhere to the following.</p><p>\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>Integrity and Authenticity</b></span></p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>To avoid any abusive practices that may affect the credibility of the company and its users, Owrners has implemented measures that would prevent the occurrence of abusive practices within our marketplace.\r\n</p><p>Any action that is intended to try to game the platform tools and features will result in the total and permanent ban of the user account(s) that engages in such conduct.\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>Account Integrity\r\n</b></span></p><p><b>Multiple Accounts\r\n</b></p><p>When using Owrners for buying and/or selling services it may be possible to have only one account. Having more than one account on Owrners is confusing to other users and is thus seen as an abuse of our system. This policy violation can result in the permanent suspension of the account(s) that participates in this activity.\r\n</p><p>It is prohibited to open multiple accounts on Owrners in order to (including but not limited to):\r\n</p><ul><li>Get an edge.\r\n</li><li>Bully/hoodwink other users through messaging and/or ordering services.\r\n</li><li>Participate in any sort of fraud.\r\n</li><li>Take advantage of the Owners Referral program.\r\n</li><li>Avoid getting a restriction or a chance to get your previous account permanently suspended.\r\n</li><li>Post, create, transmit or distribute any content that violates Owrners’ Terms of Service and/or our Community Standards in any other manner and/or attempt to manipulate the system.\r\n</li></ul><p>Never provide your genuine details like email, credit card details, phone number etc. that can be used to open multiple accounts with your identity.</p><p><b>Fake Identity</b></p><p>We don’t permit an account to impersonate someone or something in a deceitful manner.\r\n</p><p>It is prohibited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Provide a different name and gender, or any other fake information in the profile that you create with the site.\r\n</li><li>If asked to show ID, show a fake ID when doing so.\r\n</li><li>Employ fake imagery/video produced by AI to sign up and/or check the account on Owrners with the intent of identity deception.\r\n</li><li>Do not use an account under false pretenses, which means that one should not create or use an account with the purpose of deceiving other people.\r\n</li><li>Geographically spoofing is most effectively performed by utilizing automated programs and tools to provide a false location of operation.\r\n</li><li>Make an Owrners profile with your information/credentials for anyone else if not you.\r\n</li></ul><p>Never post your genuine details especially your email, your credit card details, your phone number which can be used by somebody to open fake accounts in your name. Owrners also retains the right to ban any account which is an imitation of a genuine person.\r\n</p><p><b>Misrepresentation\r\n</b></p><p>Misrepresentation is fraudulent misrepresentation, negligent misrepresentation, Innocent misrepresentation or omission of a material fact.\r\n</p><p>It is prohibited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Use fake information in the description, the profession profile, skills, professional experience, and/or education.\r\n</li><li>Do not use an Owrners seller badge, seller level or any reference to a star-rating in the Gig images, seller intro video, profile picture or in any other Gig part.\r\n</li><li>Use the content from another user’s Gig description, packages, and/or other content from their Gig listing or profile or profession profile.\r\n</li><li>Increase the price of your Gig service in the personal messages to the buyer before or after the actual purchase. Such practices as bait-and-switch marketing are prohibited.\r\n</li><li>Be represented by someone else in your Gig, or profession profile, without the other person’s identity being clearly revealed. Repost content you do not own the right to in a Gig description, user profile and/or profession profile.\r\n</li><li>Do not include ‘Owrners’ in any part of your username or display name, or pretend to be our employees with the aim of misleading the users, or engage in other prohibited activities.\r\n</li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>Inauthentic Behavior\r\n</b></span></p><p><b>Spam\r\n</b></p><p>Basically, we define spam on Owrners as an unanticipated, frequent and intrusive form of messaging. Spam can be in any form starting from mere offers to commercially oriented ones that are mainly intended to create traffic or attention to sites, products, and services other than Owrners.\r\n</p><p>Do not:\r\n</p><ul><li>Misuse our communication gadgets to spread unwanted or fake information.\r\n</li><li>Use Owrners communication tools to spread malware, phishing, or any other malicious or potentially unwanted content.\r\n</li><li>Send mass messages through any artificial tools and/or automated processes (by using software, scripts, bots and or in any other manner).\r\n</li><li>Communicate with Owrners users about some offers, questions, suggestions or any other information not related to the Gigs, requests or orders.\r\n</li><li>Get other users to show you how to go about selling on Owrners using Owrners communication tools.\r\n</li><li>Direct messaging to help buyers know more about your services or to market certain Gigs to them.\r\n</li><li>Request people for contributions in the form of money or time.\r\n</li></ul><p>This activity is detrimental to the credibility of our platform and is also invasive and possibly dangerous to the privacy of the members. In case of spam, please, do report it.\r\n</p><p><b>Feedback Manipulation\r\n</b></p><p>Reviews given by buyers are a component of Owrners’ rating system since they help to determine the company’s reputation. They express the nature of services offered by the sellers, their expertise and experience and the level of satisfaction of buyers. Therefore, the information stated in reviews has to be genuine and accurate, so that the marketplace remains truthful and credible. \r\n</p><p>Do not:\r\n</p><ul><li>In any form twist the review system to display fake information regarding the seller and/or his/her service as a buyer or a seller.\r\n</li><li>Intentionally give fake, unwanted comments.\r\n</li><li>Acquire or sell a service just for the purpose of inflating the ratings and/or levels.\r\n</li><li>Force a buyer to delete or change feedback or a review from the platform\r\n</li><li>Force a buyer into writing or saying something positive about your product that they are not willing to do or write.\r\n</li><li>Delay and deny the delivery of service or any other data necessary to finish the service with the purpose of receiving good feedbacks.\r\n</li><li>Demand that a seller provide additional services or alter something not required in the ordered service by threatening to provide a bad review.\r\n</li></ul><p>It is strictly prohibited to try to influence the reviews, and for this, all accounts connected with such an action will be permanently banned. This involves either direct or indirect interference with the feedback by providing fake, misleading or unoriginal information, placing orders that were known to be pre-arranged or inserted to inflate the sellers’ rating or by abusing the system by making purchases from another account.\r\n</p><p>In case you have any doubts about the feedback manipulation or any other violations of these policies, please, do report it.\r\n</p><p><b>Reporting Abuse\r\n</b></p><p>On Owrners, all the members of the community are welcome and respected and we do not tolerate racism, sexism or any other type of discrimination. We promote among our community members to report to us anything that is considered unacceptable.\r\n</p><p>However, we request you not to misuse these tools in such a manner that, it leads to the generation of false complaints.\r\n</p><p>Do not:\r\n</p><ul><li>Misuse reporting tools by the Abuse Owrners, fake complains to Customer Support and appeals by filing reports that are groundless, targeted, litigious or frivolous.\r\n</li><li>Send several reports about the same incident without giving our Trust and Safety team the chance to investigate the matter.\r\n</li></ul><p>Owrners retains the right to delete multiple invalid reports and block the accounts associated with it.\r\n</p><p><b>Referral Abuse\r\n</b></p><p>Owners Referral program is a great way to earn money for you and your friends if they join Owrners using your invitation. This means that the referral program will be abused when a number of accounts which have been developed with the intention of manipulating the system will refer to each other with an intention of receiving the referral bonus.\r\n</p><p>Do not:\r\n</p><ul><li>Open other accounts in other social sites in order to get some referral credit.\r\n</li><li>Try to cheat or game the existing referral program.\r\n</li></ul><p>Owrners has the discretion to cancel the accounts that participate in violation of Referral program rules on a permanent basis.\r\n</p><p><b>Manipulation\r\n</b></p><p>All the misconduct that seeks to exploit the Owrners platform tools and systems is against the values of Owrners and is detrimental to the whole Owrners community. In our bid to establish a marketplace that is credible and respectable, kindly do not try to evade the measures that have been set down to protect platform and marketplace credibility.\r\n</p><p>This includes, but is not limited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Excessive cancellations practice.\r\n</li><li>Employing the delivery button to make a delivery that is incomplete, partial, or an empty one.\r\n</li><li>Making several requests to do with an issue in question at a time without waiting for a response from our Customer Support team.\r\n</li></ul><p>Any attempts to use the platform through unauthorized means, influence and manipulate the Owrners ranking system, send fake web traffic to Gigs, sell/buy Owrners accounts, collect data on the platform, or impact the security and integrity of the marketplace in any way are prohibited.\r\n</p><p><b>Illegal and Prohibited Services\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners is a platform of free supply and demand where people can post any services they need or provide any services by themselves. However, for a number of reasons, we allow only certain types of services on Owrners. Some services can be potentially dangerous for our users in terms of privacy or their financial situation; while others are just against our policies and values.\r\n</p><p>It is important to note that all examples mentioned below are not limited to the list. We may time to time change the definition of an Illegal or prohibited service. We may also act in response to a violation of the spirit of this policy – if we come across a new threat or harm that may not be captured below. \r\n</p><p><b>Illegal Services\r\n</b></p><p>In addition, our users are expected to follow all rules and regulation that are in force. Users may not offer or request services related to an unlawful activity, or the services that support, endorse or facilitate any unlawful process. Owrners has the right to block the accounts of users who participate in violation of this policy on a permanent basis. \r\n</p><p>For the safety of our community, Owrners will not tolerate any form of illicit and unlawful actions and conduct in the platform. If you come across an item that seems to be in contravene of these policies, please do not hesitate to report it.\r\n</p><p>You will also notice that Owrners has the right to report any unlawful activity to the relevant law enforcement agencies.\r\n</p><p><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Prohibited Services</span>\r\n</b></p><p><b>Services with the potential to cause harm to our users      \r\n</b></p><p>To safeguard the interests of the Owrners community, we don’t permit any services or engagements that can purposefully or accidentally harm the users, other people, assets, or animals. This includes physical injury, posing a potential threat to the welfare of the society, infringement on individuals’ rights and freedoms etc.\r\n</p><p>Do not offer, agree to provide, or ask for services that are meant to cause harm, including but not limited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Soliciting or encouraging the prohibited and hazardous products (firearms, ammunition, drugs, and controlled substances), or the manufacturing, usage or selling of such products\r\n</li><li>Any form of sexual exploitation, abuse or any human trafficking regardless of the type.\r\n</li><li>They include the production of forged or fake documents such as ID, passports, driver’s licenses, bank statements, death or birth certificates or any kind of alteration to any of these documents.\r\n</li><li>Any content that is connected with glorification and/or encouragement of violence and/or any other unlawful and destructive activity against a person, group or animals\r\n</li><li>The desire to produce or disseminate fake news and disinformation.\r\n</li><li>Offering the licensed professional services without the necessary licenses and/ or qualifications, for example. lawyer, accountants or any other professional service providers such as financial or tax advisors.\r\n</li><li>Attempts to penetrate any type of system (accounts, profiles, networks, etc. ) with the aim of gaining unlawful access to personal and/or financial data of people or companies and/or state bodies.\r\n</li><li>Forcing or participating in creating any information security threat for people, organizations, governments (DDoS attacks, doxing, identity theft, sharing of viruses, phishing and other hack methods, etc). \r\n</li></ul><p>Any user account that has been implicated in violation of this policy will be blocked permanently.\r\n</p><p><b>Services that can pose financial risks for our users        \r\n</b></p><p>Owrners has an interest in the financial security of our users and ensures the privacy of the users’ personal financial details. Any services that are likely to expose our users to reveal their financial details are prohibited.\r\n</p><p>Do not offer, agree to provide, or ask for the services that require getting access to other user’s sensitive financial information, such as:\r\n</p><ul><li>Opening, operating, or making alterations of any sort to a monetary account of any sort\r\n</li><li>Extending a loan, or purchasing or selling currency or crypto currency or engaging in binary options or any other financial instruments.\r\n</li><li>Mining cryptocurrency.\r\n</li><li>Erasing the negative remarks from the credit score or credit history of a person, an entity or a government institution or any other credit repair service.\r\n</li><li>Trading signals, indicators or some ready-made trading plans.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Services that infringe third parties’ terms of service\r\n</b></p><p>A third party is an entity, or a person, other than Owrners, who has an indirect stake within the services you provide or seek. Being a member of our Owrners community, we kindly request you to be polite to the rest of the Internet community and adhere to the TOS of other services and companies.   \r\n</p><p>This means that you should not offer, accept or request for services that are against the TOS or may infringe TOS of a third party. \r\n</p><p>Before developing a Gig or profession page, we advise all sellers to read the terms of service of any third party involved in the service. We also advise buyers not to ask for services or order Gigs that would be prohibited under a third party’s terms of service. Owrners will not be held responsible for any action taken against users, which is in violation of the terms of service of third parties.  \r\n</p><p><b>Services which violate intellectual property rights\r\n</b></p><p>As per the various laws and more importantly to protect the work of creative community, Owrners does not allow any service that infringes the IP rights of individuals and/or businesses and shall take action against those who offer or demand such services, and thereby safeguard our creative community.\r\n</p><p>You can read more about services that infringe on the rights of intellectual property.\r\n</p><p>Misleading or Deceptive Services\r\n</p><p>In order to prevent any fraudulent activities in our community, Owrners bans the services which are aimed at misleading, manipulating or providing fake and unoriginal content.  \r\n</p><p>Do not offer, agree to provide, or ask for any services intended to mislead or deceive others, including:\r\n</p><p><b>Deep-fakes\r\n</b></p><p>Any video, photo or audio record, based on which its sequence or composition has been changed significantly, or based on which the original audio has been modified in a way that alters the essence of the original media, its meaning or context (including those created with the help of generative AI tools and programs).\r\n</p><p>Because of the potential in sharing fake news, lewd images and videos, and illicit activities through deep-fake methodologies, Owrners has a policy against making any deep-fakes on the platform. \r\n</p><p><b>Fake reviews\r\n</b></p><p>Any kind of a positive, neutral or negative review regardless of the type – written, video, etc. – that is not an independent and objective opinion or that is based on the author’s experience with the product, service, or business in question.\r\n</p><p>Any user account that will be found to be participating in violation of this policy will be terminated permanently.\r\n</p><p><b>Fake engagement or traffic\r\n</b></p><p>Anything that involves the use of fake accounts such as bots, click farms and any other unlawful methods aimed at achieving followers, views, likes, fans or traffic. All such techniques are in clear violation to third parties’ terms of services and practices and erode the credibility and trust of our site. \r\n</p><p><b>Promising financial or personal benefits\r\n</b></p><p>Anything which guarantees monetary or personal returns that are beyond the seller’s influence as well as any unrealistic or exaggerated statements that a buyer is likely to reap if they purchase the services of a seller.\r\n</p><p>This includes but is not limited to guarantees or promises related to: \r\n</p><ul><li>Regaining control of buyer’s accounts on social media sites such as amazon, Facebook, eBay and among others.\r\n</li><li>Actual or nominal dollars or actual or nominal percentage of profit/return on investment\r\n</li><li>Points, more levels, coins or dollars in any game or application\r\n</li><li>Findings connected to cure or treatment of diseases or conditions or any other promise of manipulating the mind.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Academic and Workplace Dishonesty\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners strictly prohibits any form of academic or workplace dishonesty, including the commissioning of work that will be presented as the individual\'s own effort. To that extent, Owrners strictly bans all kinds of academic or workplace fraudulence, including the ordering of work that is to be submitted as the writer’s own work. To that extent, Owrners does not permit any services that promise to do something, whether it is homework, tests or job screening assignments, which should not be done without help from outside.\r\n</p><p>Regarding any type of academic or workplace service, users are supposed to adhere to the honor code and/or internal policies of the users’ academic institution or workplace. We stress the preservation of the academic and the workplace or any other applicable code of conduct and adhere to the principles of academic and professional ethics. \r\n</p><p>Owrners will not condone any activities that degrade the academic or workplace integrity, especially those that are fraudulent, untruthful and unethical.\r\n</p><p>It is prohibited to provide or give, accept or demand undertaking of homework, completion of examinations, tests, job application questions or any other work which is supposed to be solved without help. \r\n</p><p>For more information on Academic and workplace dishonesty services please click here.\r\n</p><p><b>Services that involve sharing personal information of third parties \r\n</b></p><p>Owrners acts in a way that it prevents violation of privacy rights in a bid to safeguard the rights of its users. To guarantee this policy, we have requested that the information provided within the services relevant to the respective field, is unique to each order, and contains only business data. \r\n</p><p>Do not offer, agree to provide, or ask for any services that breach third-party rights and lead to spamming individuals, such as:\r\n</p><ul><li>Even the sharing of personal data of individuals, for instance, addresses and phone numbers and the like.\r\n</li><li>Lists which are already prepared and contain the personal details of people.\r\n</li><li>Spamming the social media sites in order to get information about other people.\r\n</li><li>Any service that discloses personal data that are of a private nature, for example, social security numbers, identification cards, credit cards, physical addresses, and so forth.\r\n</li></ul><p>Medical-related services\r\n</p><p>As a result of this policy to safeguard the Owrners community, we do not permit services that are intended to offer any medical treatment, medical consultation, medical or pharmaceutical products. This is in regard to both the health welfare of the users as well as the psychological well-being of the users. \r\n</p><p>Do not offer, agree to provide, or ask for any medical-related services, such as:Do not offer, agree to provide, or ask for any medical-related services, such as:\r\n</p><ul><li>Any treatment, suggestion on the medical condition, or information on a particular medicine.\r\n</li><li>Any kind of medical drugs or pharmaceuticals, medical equipment or pharmaceutical supply.\r\n</li><li>Presenting fake documents or any other evidence which is intended to mislead other people regarding the person’s health condition, for instance. fraudulent test results, etc.\r\n</li><li>Promising to cure, mitigate or alleviate the effects of, cancer, diabetes, eating disorders, depression, COVID-19, any other disease or medical condition including emotional therapy.\r\n</li><li>Writing only medical, scientific, or informative texts that are related to COVID-19 and can be used for the purpose of misinformation.\r\n</li><li>Disseminating of fake news or the creation of fake news relating to COVID-19.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Services outside the Owrners Catalog\r\n</b></p><p>The Owrners catalog is now online and is rather diverse and represents very fast processes occurring in the digital space. We are constantly looking forward to ensure our platform offers services that are in high demand today. For this reason, we might sometimes rearrange our catalog and may decide to discontinue offering some of the services. If you are offering one of the aforementioned services, we will inform you if your Gig has been deleted. This may be a good time to update your products and services and offer what buyers are seeking for in the market.\r\n</p><p>Additional information can be found at the Owrners Forum and our Help Center containing useful tips and articles regarding Gig creation that would be beneficial for buyers.\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><b>Objectionable Content and User Safety</b></span>\r\n</p><p><b>Adult Content and Sexual Activity\r\n</b></p><p>Any content which is intended to be sexually stimulating is prohibited on Owrners. Any sexually explicit content that is detected or reported will be blocked and some of the participants may be barred from the marketplace. Prejudicial, obscene, vulgar or patently offensive gigs, deliveries and portfolio projects depicting violence, gore or degrading fetishes are also prohibited.\r\n</p><p>Child sexual exploitation material and material that is likely to sexually exploit children is not allowed on Owrners. We flag Child Sexual Abuse Material (CSAM) to the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children, who collaborate with law enforcement all around the world.\r\n</p><p>Do not post, offer or ask for:\r\n</p><ul><li>Sexual or adult related pictures, or videos\r\n</li><li>Sex or sexual partners\r\n</li><li>Sex talks or talk\r\n</li><li>Sextortion or non-consensual production of images and videos\r\n</li><li>Child/or child-like sex\r\n</li><li>Sexual assault or slut-shaming\r\n</li><li>Sexually charged modeling\r\n</li><li>The carrying out of fetish scenarios\r\n</li><li>Any material that shows sexual conduct, save for the circumstances that apply to the ‘documentary exception’, mentioned below.\r\n</li></ul><p>Owners will not hesitate to suspend the transactions with the child nudity and report the account for further investigation.\r\n</p><p><b>Documentary Exception\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners will permit bareness in situations where its main objective is educational, scientific or artistic, and not otherwise. For instance, a video edit of a film that was ordered by a midwife showing the correct way of breast feeding is acceptable while making a video montage of clips from the same film for the purpose of sexual arousal is not acceptable. The use of nudity from indigenous peoples, protests, surgeries, deliveries, art, breast feeding or similar may not fall under our documentary exception. \r\n</p><p><b><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Hate Speech and Discrimination</span>\r\n</b></p><p><b>Hate Speech\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners explains hate speech as communication that is likely to promote violence or hatred towards an individual or a group of people depending on their characteristics, as perceived or as they are, in that they can be based on race, skin color, ethnicity, sexual orientation, gender, marital status, religion, age, or disability.\r\n</p><p>Hate speech may also refer to threats, obscenities, and depersonalization or as content that uses ethnic or racial epithets or as content that celebrates or advocates for hatred.\r\n</p><p>Owrners is keen to act fast and appropriately when it comes to the conduct that has been reported and/or alleged to be hate speech, and will act in a way that reflects the company’s policy and Terms of Service. We are extremely sensitive to hate speech violation and may be flexible in handling any user or content that violates this policy.\r\n</p><p><b>Do not:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Employ hatred and/or low tones words against a person or any group of people based on their actual or assumed race, ethnicity, color, sexual orientation, gender, marital status, religion, age, or disability\r\n</li><li>Employ ethnically or racially insensitive language\r\n</li><li>Employ hate speech towards another community member(s), group of people, Owrners’s Customer Support representatives, or Owrners as a company\r\n</li><li>Promote, accept to deliver, or request material that is inclined towards hate speech\r\n</li><li>Affirm or praise hate groups, its members, their activities, or any of the beliefs that the hate groups hold.\r\n</li><li>Post or transmit any content on the Owrners platform (such as profile page, Gig description, profession page, portfolio project, forum thread, brief and so on) that contains hate images, including hate symbols associated with such groups as swastikas, hand signs, or numbers that are identified as symbols of hate or discrimination.\r\n</li></ul><p>We do allow users to offer or ask for related content that is intended to contribute to:\r\n</p><ul><li>The study or increase people’s awareness of hate speech\r\n</li><li>Preventing hate speech practices.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Discrimination\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners defines discrimination as any unfair or unequal treatment of a person or group of people based on their actual or perceived race, skin color, ethnic origin, sexual orientation, gender, marital status, religion, age or disability.\r\n</p><p>Likewise, if the employee’s personal attributes or qualities other than service delivery impact on the favoritism that may deny others on the platform equal opportunities, then such favoritism would also be considered discriminatory.\r\n</p><p><b>Do not:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Decline contact and/or cooperation with a person or a group of people due to real or assumed traits including but not limited to race, skin color, ethnicity, sexual orientation, gender, marital status, religion, age, or disability\r\n</li><li>Provide or request any content which promotes, advocates, or encourages discrimination based on race, ethnicity, or other protected characteristics or any group or person that supports these ideas or actions.\r\n</li></ul><p>If you find that there is any form of behavior or content that you think goes against this policy, please do report it. Owners will necessarily examine complaints of discrimination individually, and profiles that are associated with violation of this policy may be deleted permanently.\r\n</p><p>Harassment and Abusive Conduct \r\n</p><p>Owrners does not allow any and all acts of harassment and any form of communication that is deemed as such. This includes, but is not limited to:This includes, but is not limited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Bullying\r\n</li><li>Sexual advances\r\n</li><li>Offensive comments/conduct\r\n</li><li>Discrimination of people by their actual or assumed attributes such as race, color, ethnicity, sexual orientation, gender, marital status, religion, age or disability.\r\n</li></ul><p>When communicating on Owrners,<b> do not:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Ask any sexual contact\r\n</li><li>Make other people the center of attention of your questions\r\n</li><li>Being sexually concerned or sexually suggestive\r\n</li><li>Swear, make obscene, vulgar or slanderous gestures\r\n</li><li>Offend anyone/any culture or minority or use any sexually explicit language\r\n</li><li>Send obscene or objectionable articles.\r\n</li></ul><p>Also, the sellers are not allowed to share buyers’ data, including any personal data, to third parties (unless with the consent of the buyer). Any violation of the rights of the users to privacy or confidentiality may result in the permanent deletion of the accounts.\r\n</p><p>If you experience any form of behavior that you think is in violation of this policy, you should make a complaint.\r\n</p><p><b>Self-Harm and Suicide \r\n</b></p><p>At Owrners, the welfare of the community is our utmost priority, and this is why we are very much concerned with safety. For that reason, users should not provide, accept, or request any content that depicts, encourages, or endorses suicide and/or other self- destructive behaviors, such as eating disorders.\r\n</p><p>In case the person you’re conversing with is in any way talking about suicide or any kind of self-harm, we kindly request you to call the local authorities and report the case.\r\n</p><p>If you are in a vulnerable state or experiencing an emotionally taxing period or if you are thinking about suicide or self-harm, please do not hesitate to ask for help.\r\n</p><p><b>Violence and Unlawful Behavior\r\n</b></p><p><b>Violence and Incitement\r\n</b></p><p>Safety of the community is our priority and it means that we have to take each and every threat of violence seriously. This includes being able to prevent any possible harm that may be inflicted to our community or to other people outside the platform. We will use language and context to determine realistic threats and act on those who violate this policy. We may also inform the police when there is a threat to the lives or physical well being of individuals.\r\n</p><p>Incitement means to provoke or urge other people to participate in unlawful activities. Bear in mind that even if you request other people to commit a crime, it may also be unlawful no matter the response to the request. Other examples of unlawful actions include celebration, or praising/condoning violence, which is a type of violence; it is a type of abuse that is practiced to show power. All of the above actions are prohibited on Owrners. \r\n</p><p><b>Do not:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Use violence against another community member(s), group of people, Owrners employees or Owrners a company.\r\n</li><li>Make any threats of physical violence against an individual, a group or animals (ex. murders, mass shootings, animal sacrifices, spells/sorcery with malicious intent, etc. )\r\n</li><li>Post anything that promotes such actions or violence upon other people or supports violence (such as genocide, terrorism, etc.)\r\n</li><li>Post pictures with symbols which are associated with violent ideologies such as swastikas, hand symbols, or numbers like 88 that is associated with hate, etc.\r\n</li><li>Include or request any content that is menacing, violent or supportive of violence against people, groups or population in general.\r\n</li><li>Encourage someone (with invitations or commands) to commit a crime or perform actions which are criminal or possibly criminal.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Dangerous Organizations and Individuals\r\n</b></p><p>On Owrners, we do not permit content or actions that are associated with or promote, endorse, or advocate for dangerous groups, their members, their activities, or their beliefs. This is because most of the organizations have taken to the use of the internet to pass their agenda, spread the messages of hate and recruit more members to join their group.\r\n</p><p>This includes, but is not limited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Al Qaeda, ISIS, Boko Haram, Al Shabbab, and other groups as well as homegrown terror groups.\r\n</li><li>Mafia and terrorist groups\r\n</li><li>Some of the radical groups and persons\r\n</li><li>Hate/conspiracy groups.\r\n</li></ul><p>Owrners also retains the right to cancel the accounts of users that are found guilty of violation of this policy.\r\n</p><p><b>Do not:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Encourage violence/violence-related activities, hate speech, dangerous ideologies or a call to action, or conspiracy theories\r\n</li><li>Condone or praise dangerous organizations, their individuals, their activities, or their beliefs\r\n</li><li>Recommend, accept to supply, or request services connected to activities of dangerous groups and/or their members or associated beliefs\r\n</li><li>Services which incite violence, conspiracy theories, or propaganda or services that support/propose the activity of the above organizations or offer or agree to provide services.\r\n</li></ul><p>We do allow users to offer or ask for related services that are intended to contribute to:\r\n</p><ul><li>The investigation of dangerous groups and organizations\r\n</li><li>The prevention of terror, the ban on extremists and criminals.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Misinformation and Fake News\r\n</b></p><p>It is information that is wrong or contains wrong data which is either passed unknowingly or when it is passed with wrong intention (disinformation). Since misinformation can be damaging for the individuals and the general public, Owners will not tolerate attempts of misinformation spreading through the platform and/or to the general public. Any user account which will be involved in this kind of act will be banned for a long time from the platform.\r\n</p><p>Fake news refers to a situation whereby information is created and when presented in an article or story format with the purpose of deceiving or spreading propaganda.\r\n</p><p><b>Do not transmit, accept to provide, or request services that generate, disseminate, or advertise fake news and misinformation particularly in political content. \r\n</b></p><p>This extends to services that use generative AI tools and/or programs to create, promote, or distribute such content, and includes, but is not limited to the following for the purposes of spreading misinformation at scale:\r\n</p><ul><li>Deepfakes in videos, photos or audio and voice cloning.\r\n</li><li>Mechanized procedures (programs, macros, robots, etc.)\r\n</li></ul><p>We do allow to users to offer or ask for related services that are intended to contribute to:\r\n</p><ul><li>The study of different methods of propaganda and fake news.\r\n</li><li>The prevention of generation and dissemination of fake news and information.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Election Integrity and Political Content \r\n</b></p><p>On Owrners, we respect people and their opinions, and do not tolerate discrimination of any kind, negative attitudes towards other people, or censorship of any kind. To preserve these principles and ensure the safety of all the users of the Owrners marketplace, we do not allow attempts to interfere with the elections and other referendums.\r\n</p><p>Election interference means any act that seeks to disrupt the electoral process or to compromise and erode the people’s trust in democratic elections.\r\n</p><p><b>Do not:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Propose, accept to render, or request services that disrupt elections or other democratic processes\r\n</li><li>Disseminate incorrect information as to procedures in election processes\r\n</li><li>Stir a riot, sabotage, or destroy processes and/or election systems or advocate for violent action and threats.\r\n</li><li>Establish fake profiles to deceive a candidate, an elected official, a political party, or a government body of an affiliation which is not true—or post content that is meant to deceive a candidate, an elected official, a political party, or a government body of an affiliation which is not real.\r\n</li><li>Employ generative AI tools and/or programs to generate or disseminate content, which in any of the above forms, seeks to subvert an election or other democratic process.\r\n</li></ul><p>This is to say that we do permit the users to post offers or requests for related services that are meant to be advertised as caricature, satire, parody, or meme.\r\n</p><p><b>Intellectual Property\r\n</b></p><p><b>Intellectual Property Claims (Copyright (DMCA), Trademark Infringement)\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners Corporate has a zero-tolerance policy towards violation of Intellectual Property (IP) rights and recognizes the IP rights of third parties. For this purpose, it is necessary to have necessary mechanisms for the protection of intellectual property rights.\r\n</p><p>Since the content uploaded to Owrners’ platform by our users is User Generated Content (UGC), we developed and launched specific flows for the notification of IPR infringement (copyright and trademark).\r\n</p><p>Once a report of all relevant information is received from a rights holder or authorized representative (“reporter”), we will remove or disable access to content that engages in:\r\n</p><ul><li>Copyright infringement\r\n</li><li>Trademark infringement\r\n</li></ul><p>Owrners has the right to demand some extra information from a reporter, for example, the documents that prove the ownership.\r\n</p><p><b>Services Which Violate Intellectual Property Rights\r\n</b></p><p>Services which infringe the rights of creators and other legal owners of certain objects of intellectual property.\r\n</p><p>Pursuant to the provisions of the above laws—and as part of our mission to safeguard the work of the creative industry, Owners shall not allow any service that infringes on the intellectual property (IP) of persons and/or companies; Owners shall also take action against those who offer/provide or seek such services, and in so doing protect our creative industry.\r\n</p><p><b>Do not</b> offer, agree to provide, or ask for services such as:\r\n</p><ul><li>Activities involving copying or distribution of copyrighted material (digital piracy): creating torrent sites, designing platforms for streaming movies and TV shows, selling access to any streaming service account and others.\r\n</li><li>Products that include the use of cracked or hacked services such as; software products: programs, apps, themes, templates, games, and many more.\r\n</li><li>Services which are designed with the purpose of eradicating the watermark or the copyright mark in an unlawful manner.\r\n</li></ul><p>Owrners also retains the right to terminate any accounts which are involved in the infringement of intellectual property rights as a permanent measure.\r\n</p><p><b>Non-Original Design Standards\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners acknowledges people’s efforts and talent. Since it exists to help designers, artists, writers, and creative from all over the world, original content has to be put forward and provided at all times. All non-original work which may be submitted and/or delivered as original work shall be dealt with an appropriate and immediate manner.\r\n</p><p>The following standards refer to Gig listings, portfolio projects and delivered orders in the Graphics &amp; Design and Photography categories on Owrners:\r\n</p><p>Do not mimic, advertise, or distribute other people’s work as your own work..\r\n</p><p><b>Unique concept and publication\r\n</b></p><ul><li>When using existing creative components, the designers have to incorporate these components in a novel manner to come up with the new design concept.\r\n</li><li>The work that is delivered should not be something that has been copied somewhere whether online or offline, it has to be created for the first time..\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Gig images and Portfolio projects\r\n</b></p><ul><li>All designs or photos that are to be included in Gig images and portfolio projects must be original work of the seller, however, it can be work that has been posted on the designer’s websites or social media accounts before.\r\n</li><li>A designer who wants to use a design or photograph from an order delivered on Owrners must get permission from the buyer who ordered it.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Elements that can be similar\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Generic shapes: Ex. Point, line, square, ellipsoid, cone and so on.\r\n</li><li>Functional designs: Ex. A circle, a diamond, a heart, ears on a tiger, wheels on a car, green color for being an environmentally friendly company and so on.\r\n</li><li>Elements not eligible for copyright protection, such as:\r\n</li><li>Such short phrases as ‘Show me the money’ or ‘Beam me up’\r\n</li><li>Other facts and theories such as the scientific facts or the quantum theory\r\n</li><li>Concepts, but not the manner in which such a concept is formulated. For instance, the story line of comics can be a concept but not how the designer implemented the concept.\r\n</li><li>Substances generally incorporated in a work of a given category of art, for instance. Elements of an artistic work, such as castles, knights, and dragons in a medieval story; features and characteristics of creative material that are conventional or believed to be compulsory to a specific type of work.\r\n</li><li>Stock image and template policy.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Stock image and template policy\r\n</b></p><p>It is also important to make sure you have all the licenses for using the stock image or template in the delivery.\r\n</p><p><u>Stock images\r\n</u></p><ul><li>All the pictures used in this website should be obtained from the stock photo agencies.\r\n</li><li>Do not send or post stock images in their raw form.\r\n</li><li>This comes in when you are delivering your content, it can be incorporated as a transformation of the stock images.\r\n</li></ul><p><u>Templates\r\n</u></p><ul><li>In case you have used a template in your design work, ensure that your delivered design is different from the template design in terms of the look and feel, concept and/or use.\r\n</li><li>You are allowed to offer a service based on templates that can be found on the internet but this has to be stated in your Gig.\r\n</li><li>Designers who use templates in their work and rely on them a lot will not be allowed to be part of special seller programs on Owrners, for example. Owrners Pro.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Responsible Digital Creation\r\n</b></p><p>At Owrners, we strive to create a community of decent digital citizens. Works created on Owrners may frequently include third-party services or products that are intended to be utilized by third-party platforms (for instance, social networks, other marketplaces, or AI-writing tools). In such cases, we ask our users to adhere to the following guidelines:\r\n</p><p><b>Respect for Third-Party Rights\r\n</b></p><p>Users should respect the rights of third parties, which are the members of the Owrners community as well as people who are not members of the Owrners community. If you are aware that your activity or delivery on Owrners depends on other platforms or companies, then you must adhere to their TOSs and other related policies such as their privacy policy, or intellectual property policy.\r\n</p><p><b>Transparency\r\n</b></p><p>When using external elements, users have to be clear on the use of third party content, including the rights they have in regard to such content.\r\n</p><p><b>Mutual Respect\r\n</b></p><p>Sellers are urged to disclose information about the incorporation of third party items in their works, particularly in Gigs. For buyers who make orders that require deliveries to involve third parties, it is advisable to be keen and ask about the source of integrated parts especially when negotiating or making orders with sellers, so that one does not infringe on the rights of other parties.\r\n</p><p><b>Intellectual Property Protection\r\n</b></p><p>It is expected that users will respect the IP rights such as the copyrights, trademarks etc even where the content is in the public domain and one has to keep a record when working on a project or when using materials from other sources. Deliveries that are made on Owrners should not infringe the IP of other. In the cases where it is necessary, users should include licenses or permissions to confirm certain rights.\r\n</p><p>Thus, following these rules, users can help create a successful and legal online market place and creative work remains legal, open, and polite.\r\n</p><p>For further details please refer to Owrners’ Guide to Responsible Digital Creation.\r\n</p><p><b>The distinctions between using other sellers’ work in the delivery of your services and profit arbitrage\r\n</b></p><p><b>Pre-existing works can be employed in your delivery where you have the licences to do so and it is employed as part of your delivery.\r\n</b></p><p>It cannot be used as your own delivery when you are reselling it “as is” with no considerable added value or other use that transforms it into new creation under the misperception that it is an entirely original work, for the purpose of making a profit out of the price difference. That is called profit arbitrage and it is not allowed on Owrners.\r\n</p><p><b>Other sellers’ work samples that you can use </b>(provided that you have the right to reuse them).\r\n</p><ul><li>It also incorporates designs as backgrounds for music videos.\r\n</li><li>Pictures for the websites or power point.\r\n</li><li>Background music for explainer videos.\r\n</li></ul><p><b>Artificial Intelligence (AI) Generated Content\r\n</b></p><p>Owrners actively uses new technology and allows the content created by the users with the help of generative AI tools and programs.\r\n</p><p>As the users’ expectations shift to adapt to the growing use of generative AI tools and programs, sellers who apply them to create content or provide services should adhere to the following rules.\r\n</p><p><b>Sellers must:\r\n</b></p><ul><li>Make sure they have the necessary permissions for the content that they produce such as copyrights.\r\n</li></ul><p><i>If the content created and/or delivered on Owrners with the help of AI violates or is a violation of any copyrights, applicable law or Owrners’ Community Standards, such content will be deleted from the platform and the seller receives a permanent ban.\r\n</i></p><ul><li>In addition, follow the terms of service of the respective tool and/or program and all the regulations that apply such as data protection, privacy, and consumer rights.\r\n</li><li>Provide services to every order as a unique order and not provide AI content services where the same content is produced for different buyers.\r\n</li></ul><p>AI tools cannot be used by sellers and buyers for the promotion of misinformation, non-consensual content, deep fakes in any form of video, photo or audio recording, fake accounts as well as creating faces of human beings who do not exist for unlawful purposes.\r\n</p><p><b>Sellers should know the buyers’ preference about the product\r\n</b></p><p>When thinking of services that may or may not incorporate generative AI tools or programs, the buyer that has a preference for work that has been created and/or delivered without the use of generative AI tools or programs should express this to the seller. \r\n</p><p>If you have any concerns or ideas about any misuse or unethical use of generative AI, please do not hesitate to report.\r\n</p><p>As for these policies and guidelines, they will also be changed based on the current trends and usage in generative AI. Kindly, do check back for any changes that may be made from time to time.\r\n</p><p><b>Minors policy\r\n</b></p><p>The Terms of Service of Owrners state that all users must be 18 years old and of the age that is legally allowed to enter into a contract. Users below the age of 18 years, or at least 13 years are allowed to use the site only through an account owned by their parent or legal guardian with consent. Children under 13 years are not allowed to use the site.\r\n</p><p><b>Services Involving Minors\r\n</b></p><p>Certain Gigs on Owrners include the use of the minors in the provision of the services. \r\n</p><ul><li>If the minor is the main performer (for instance, child voice over) then the owner of the account has to be the child’s parent or the legal guardian. When this is the case it must be clearly indicated in the Gig components and the description of the profile.\r\n</li><li>Where the minor is involved in the creation of the service (for instance, taking photographs for children’s products) it should be apparent to the audience that the participation of a minor is necessary.   \r\n</li></ul><p>Parents or legal guardians and sellers who use the services of minors are obliged to adhere to all the rules of child labor protection in the territory of the state. \r\n</p><p>Users under 18 may not take part in providing the following services on Owrners: Dance lessons, modeling, greeting cards and videos and your message on.\r\n</p><p><b>No Sexually Explicit Content Featuring Minors\r\n</b></p><p>We do not allow sexually explicit content featuring minors or content that seeks to sexually exploit minors, including but not limited to:\r\n</p><ul><li>Such as lewd illustrations and voiceovers\r\n</li><li>erotic stories\r\n</li><li>Lolicon (or loli), shotacon (or shota) voice overs or anime illustrations\r\n</li><li>Deep-fakes\r\n</li><li>Any sexual references that are child-like such as those created by AI tools and programs.\r\n</li></ul><p>We also do not allow to display and describe the minors in the sexually provocative manner or violent or in any way that may be considered as exploitation.\r\n</p><p>Owrners may use broad discretion when exercising their discretion to remove the content that involves or contains the minor. Users’ accounts that participated in the violation of this policy may be terminated permanently.\r\n</p><p>If a user shares CSAM, we forward this information to the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children which collaborates with international police forces.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p><p> \r\n</p>',NULL,'normal_layout','none',NULL,NULL,'01','all',1,'2024-09-19 06:32:03','2024-09-19 06:32:41');
